13 CITIZENS SUPPORT ACT
14 SECTION 5.25.(a) Department of Health and Human Services. – The Department
15 of Health and Human Services is directed to do all of the following:
16 (1) To the extent permitted by federal law, the Department of Health and Human
17 Services (DHHS) shall take all steps necessary to cease providing
18 State-funded benefits to noncitizens residing in the United States without legal
19 permission.
20 (2) To the extent permitted by federal law, the DHHS shall develop and
21 implement a plan to review and update the eligibility criteria for all
22 State-funded benefits to ensure that noncitizens determined to be residing in
23 the United States without legal permission are ineligible to receive
24 State-funded benefits. As a part of this plan, the DHHS shall develop a method
25 for verifying the immigration status of applicants for State-funded benefits
26 who are noncitizens prior to the initiation of benefits.
27 (3) By January 15, 2026, the DHHS shall report to the Joint Legislative Oversight
28 Committee on Health and Human Services and the Fiscal Research Division
29 all of the following:
30 a. The steps taken to implement Section 1 of this act and the resulting
31 success of those steps.
32 b. A list of State-funded benefits for which the DHHS is prohibited from
33 changing.
34 c. The plan developed and implemented pursuant to Section 2 of this act,
35 which shall include a citation to each federal law or regulation that
36 prohibits the DHHS from denying eligibility for State-funded benefits
37 to noncitizens determined to be residing in the United States without
38 legal permission.
39 SECTION 5.25.(b) State-funded Benefits Defined. – As used in subsection (a) of
40 this section, "State-funded benefits" includes any of the following programs administered by or
41 through a contract with the DHHS but excludes any benefits or services available under these
42 programs to help eligible beneficiaries access food or meals:
43 (1) Temporary Assistance for Needy Families (Work First).
44 (2) Early Intervention Services.
45 (3) Rental or housing assistance programs.
46 (4) Medication assistance programs.
47 (5) Child care subsidy programs.
48 (6) Foster care and adoption assistance payments.
49 (7) Refugee assistance programs.
50 (8) Low Income Energy Assistance.
