17 "Part 3. Community College Programs.
18 "§ 115D-10.5. Program funding.
19 (a) New Programs and Terminations of Programs. – A community college may not offer
20 a new program without the approval of the State Board of Community Colleges except that
21 approval shall not be required if the tuition for the program will fully cover the cost of the
22 program. If at any time tuition fails to fully cover the cost of a program that falls under the
23 exception, the program shall be discontinued unless approved by the State Board. If a proposed
24 new program would serve more than one community college, the State Board shall perform a
25 feasibility study prior to acting on the proposal. The State Board shall consider whether a regional
26 approach can be used when developing new programs and, to the extent possible, shall initiate
27 new programs on a regional basis. The State Board shall collect data on an annual basis on all
28 new programs and program terminations it approved and any regionalization of programs during
29 the year, including the specific reasons for which each program was terminated or approved.
30 (b) Recreation Extension Courses. – Funds appropriated to the Community Colleges
31 System Office as operating expenses for allocation to the institutions comprising the North
32 Carolina Community College System shall not be used to support recreation extension courses.
33 The financing of these courses by any institution shall be on a self-supporting basis, and
34 membership hours produced from these activities shall not be counted when computing full-time
35 equivalent students (FTE) for use in budget-funding formulas at the State level.
36 (c) Real Estate Continuing Education Courses. – Whenever a community college offers
37 real estate continuing education courses, the courses shall be offered on a self-supporting basis.
38 "§ 115D-10.10. College transfer program approval; standards for programs; annual
39 reporting requirements.
40 (a) The State Board of Community Colleges may approve the addition of the college
41 transfer program to a community college. If addition of the college transfer program to an
42 institution would require a substantial increase in funds, State Board approval shall be subject to
