48 (a) Approval. – No course of instruction shall be offered by any community college at
49 State expense or partial State expense to any captive or co-opted group of students, as defined by
50 the State Board of Community Colleges, without prior approval of the State Board. All course
51 offerings approved for State prison inmates or prisoners in local jails must be tied to clearly
