General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (2) The student shall be given the option, when feasible, to continue classes and
2 coursework during the academic term through online participation for the
3 period of time the student is placed on active duty.
4 (3) The student shall be given the option of receiving a temporary grade of
5 "incomplete (IN)" or "absent from the final exam (AB)" for any course that
6 the student was unable to complete as a result of being placed on State active
7 duty status; however, the student must complete the course requirements
8 within the period of time specified by the community college to avoid
9 receiving a failing grade for the course.
10 (4) The student shall be permitted to drop, with no penalty, any course that the
11 student was unable to complete as a result of being placed on State active duty
12 status."
