6 EXPEDITED TEACHER PIPELINE PATHWAY STUDY
7 SECTION 6.8. No later than March 15, 2026, ApprenticeshipNC shall report to the
8 Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee on a plan to facilitate one or more expedited
9 pathways for apprenticeship candidates to enter the teaching profession. ApprenticeshipNC shall
10 develop the plan in collaboration with the Board of Governors of The University of North
11 Carolina, the State Board of Community Colleges, the Department of Public Instruction, and
12 Teach NC. In addition, ApprenticeshipNC may, in its discretion, collaborate with representatives
13 of approved educator preparation programs, local school administrative units, and existing
14 apprenticeship programs. The plan shall include at least the following components:
15 (1) Options for an accelerated transition pathway that allows high school students
16 to earn college credits leading to a teaching license while participating in
17 structured, paid, or other experiential learning in the classroom, including
18 applicable program design and sequencing components needed to achieve that
19 goal.
20 (2) Maximize usage and transferability of at least the following coursework
21 completion opportunities:
22 a. College transfer pathways provided through the Career and College
23 Promise Program that support entry into a recognized educator
24 preparation program.
25 b. Community college coursework leading to completion of an associate
26 degree related to teacher preparation.
27 c. Online or asynchronous coursework provided at a constituent
28 institution of The University of North Carolina leading to a bachelor's
29 degree.
30 d. Enrollment in an associate degree program or a bachelor's degree
31 program while serving (i) as a full-time employee in a public school
32 unit and (ii) as a teacher assistant or apprentice in a registered
33 apprenticeship program pursuant to G.S. 115C-269.33, as enacted by
34 Section 7.37 of this act.
35 (3) Any legislative changes or appropriations needed to implement the plan.
