26 DIGITAL CREDENTIAL PILOT PROGRAM
27 SECTION 6.11.(a) There is established the Digital Credential Pilot Program
28 (Program) for the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium. The purpose of the Program is to evaluate the
29 effectiveness of digital credential vaults for use by community college students. The North
30 Carolina Community Colleges System Office shall contract with a third-party entity to create a
31 secure, interoperable digital vault platform capable of issuing, storing, verifying, and sharing
32 learner credentials, including microcredentials, certifications, transcripts, and verified skill
33 records and credentials. The platform shall provide equitable cross-device access for learners and
34 allow for credential portability across educational institutions and employers, support open
35 standards for interoperability, offer real-time verification, and ensure privacy and security in
36 compliance with applicable laws. The system shall enable learners to manage a comprehensive,
37 lifelong record of achievement that is accessible, verifiable, and shareable with third parties
38 through digital means. Vault data must be user-encrypted to prevent unauthorized access or sale,
39 and all credential and learner data shall be owned and controlled by the student.
40 SECTION 6.11.(b) The System Office shall select six community colleges to
41 participate in the Program. The System Office shall make an application available to all
42 community colleges for participation in the Program no later than 30 days after this section
43 becomes law. Community colleges may submit applications up to 30 days after the application
44 is made available. The System Office shall select community colleges to participate in the
45 Program no later than 30 days after the close of the application window.
46 SECTION 6.11.(c) The System Office shall conduct a study on the efficacy of
47 raising student fees to continue the Program beyond the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium. The System
48 Office shall report to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee on the results of the
49 study by January 15, 2027.
