15 "§ 115C-77.1. Cell phone-free education policy.
16 (a) Governing bodies of public school units shall adopt a cell phone-free education policy
17 to eliminate or severely restrict student access to cell phones during instructional time.
18 (b) The cell phone-free education policy shall allow student use of cell phones during
19 instructional time as follows:
20 (1) If authorized by a teacher for educational purposes. The governing body may
