11 TEACHER APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM
12 SECTION 7.37.(a) Article 17D of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended
13 by adding a new section to read:
14 "§ 115C-269.33. Teacher Apprenticeship Program.
15 (a) Definitions. – The following definitions shall apply in this section:
16 (1) Advanced Teaching Roles unit. – As defined in G.S. 115C-310.3(6).
17 (2) Apprentice. – A person who is employed as an apprentice by an apprenticeship
18 employer and meets all of the following criteria:
19 a. Holds a bachelor's degree.
20 b. Is eligible to hold or holds one of the following:
21 1. An emergency license.
22 2. A residency license.
23 3. A permit to teach issued by the Department in accordance with
24 rules adopted by the State Board of Education.
25 c. Submitted a Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA).
26 (3) Apprenticeship employer. – An Advanced Teaching Roles unit that meets all
27 of the following criteria:
28 a. Has a registered apprenticeship program under requirements
29 established by the United States Department of Labor.
30 b. Employs apprentices under the Program.
31 (4) Department. – The Department of Public Instruction.
32 (5) Program. – The Teacher Apprenticeship Program.
33 (6) RFP. – Request for proposals.
34 (b) Program Established; Purpose. – There is established the Teacher Apprenticeship
35 Program as a competitive grant program for the purpose of increasing the number of
36 professionally licensed teachers in the State and improving teacher competency, student
37 outcomes, and teacher retention in the State. The Department of Public Instruction shall
38 administer the Program in collaboration with ApprenticeshipNC as set forth in this section.
39 (c) Request for Proposals. – No later than November 1 of each year, ApprenticeshipNC
40 shall issue an RFP for the Program. Advanced Teaching Roles units may submit proposals by
41 January 1 of the following calendar year. Proposals shall include at least the following
42 information:
43 (1) A plan to establish a registered teacher apprenticeship program in
44 collaboration with ApprenticeshipNC, including at least the following
45 information:
46 a. The number of apprentices the unit intends to employ using grant
47 funds for State-funded salary supplements, State-funded enrollment
48 expenses, or both.
49 b. Specific subject areas and grade levels in the local school
50 administrative unit with teacher shortages.
