39 CTE MODERNIZATION
40 SECTION 7.38.(a) Of the funds appropriated to the Department of Public
41 Instruction in this act, up to two million five hundred thousand dollars ($2,500,000) in
42 nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year and two million dollars ($2,000,000) in
43 nonrecurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year shall be used to create a grant program for
44 modernization of Career and Technical Education (CTE) programming, materials, training, and
45 professional development for courses conducted in grades six through 12. The Department shall
46 establish a grant program for each school year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to which a public
47 school unit or regional partnership of more than one public school unit may apply to receive
48 funds if a school within the unit or partnership has an existing CTE program. Grant recipients
49 shall use the funds distributed to them under this section to procure and implement an online
50 digital CTE learning platform containing comprehensive courses with lesson plans, media-rich
51 content and activities, and interactive assessments that align with the North Carolina Career and
Page 128 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 Technical Education Standards. The platform shall have modules that assist teachers in preparing
2 students for high-wage, high-growth career areas. By October 1, 2025, the Department shall
