30 "§ 115C-81.95. Elementary performing arts education.
31 Each local school administrative unit shall provide all students in kindergarten through grade
32 five instruction in music, dance, or theatre arts that aligns with the Standard Course of Study.
33 The instruction shall meet at least the following criteria:
34 (1) Occur during at least one instructional day out of every five instructional days.
35 (2) Be taught by at least one licensed music, dance, or theatre arts education
36 instructor.
37 (3) Instructional sessions shall last at least 30 consecutive minutes.
38 (4) Instructional sessions shall be given to classes no larger than the maximum
39 classroom size per instructional session for each grade, as provided in
40 G.S. 115C-301.
41 "§ 115C-81.96. Elementary visual arts education.
42 Each local school administrative unit shall provide all students in kindergarten through grade
43 five instruction in the visual arts that aligns with the Standard Course of Study. The instruction
44 shall meet at least the following criteria:
45 (1) Occur during at least one instructional day out of every five instructional days.
46 (2) Be taught by at least one licensed visual arts education instructor.
47 (3) Instructional sessions shall last at least 30 consecutive minutes.
48 (4) Instructional sessions shall be given to classes no larger than the maximum
49 classroom size per instructional session for each grade, as provided in
50 G.S. 115C-301."
