16 prevailing party shall be awarded all costs of such litigation, including
17 reasonable attorneys' fees. The remedies herein shall not be the exclusive
18 remedies of the Commission. The Commission may pursue any other
19 remedies available under federal or the defaulting Member State's law.
20 (2) A Member State may initiate legal action against the Commission in the U.S.
21 District Court for the District of Columbia or the federal district where the
22 Commission has its principal offices to enforce compliance with the
23 provisions of the Compact and its promulgated Rules. The relief sought may
24 include both injunctive relief and damages. In the event judicial enforcement
25 is necessary, the prevailing party shall be awarded all costs of such litigation,
26 including reasonable attorneys' fees.
27 (3) No person other than a Member State shall enforce this Compact against the
