26 "§ 115C-301. Allocation of teachers; class size.
27 …
28 (c) Maximum Class Size for Kindergarten Through Third Grade. – The average class size
29 for kindergarten through third grade in a local school administrative unit shall be as follows:
30 (1) Growing local school administrative units. – If a local school administrative
31 unit has an increase in student population of one-half percent (0.5%) of the
32 average daily membership of the local school administrative unit for two
33 consecutive years, then the unit shall be considered a growing local school
34 administrative unit for the two years immediately following the second year
35 of student population increase. Growing local school administrative units may
36 exceed the allotment ratios listed in subdivision (2) of this subsection by up to
37 three students.
38 (2) All other local school administrative units. – For any local school
39 administrative unit not qualifying as growing under subdivision (1) of this
40 subsection, the average class size for kindergarten through third grade in the
41 local school administrative unit shall at no time exceed the funded allotment
42 ratio of teachers to students in kindergarten through third grade. At the end of
43 the second school month and for the remainder of the school year, the size of
44 an individual class in kindergarten through third grade shall not exceed the
45 allotment ratio by more than three students. The funded class size allotment
46 ratio for kindergarten through third grade shall be as follows:
47 (1)a. For kindergarten, one teacher per 18 students.
48 (2)b. For first grade, one teacher per 16 students.
49 (3)c. For second grade, one teacher per 17 students.
50 (4)d. For third grade, one teacher per 17 students.
