1 AFTER SCHOOL ROBOTICS GRANT PROGRAM
2 SECTION 7.51.(a) Program; Purpose. – To the extent funds are made available for
3 the purpose, there is established the Educational and Competitive After-School Robotics Grant
4 Program (Program) for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium. The purpose of the Program
5 shall be to (i) promote evidence-based, after-school programs for robotics education and
6 competition and (ii) motivate students to pursue education and career opportunities in science,
7 technology, engineering, and mathematics while building critical life and work-related skills.
8 SECTION 7.51.(b) Eligibility. – Any public school unit is eligible to apply to the
9 Department of Public Instruction for a grant to develop an educational and competitive
10 after-school robotics program with a robotics partner in any high school within the public school
11 unit. As used in this subsection, the term "robotics partner" shall refer to a third-party entity, such
12 as a nonprofit organization or institution of higher education, approved by the Department of
13 Public Instruction that is able to provide adequate support for an after-school robotics program.
14 In order to provide adequate support, a robotics partner must meet at least all of the following
15 criteria:
16 (1) Have a national presence in robotics education and competition.
17 (2) Provide adequate instruction and programming for students and adult
18 volunteers in (i) robotics education, (ii) project-based learning, and (iii)
19 competitive robotics.
20 (3) Promote a safe and equitable social environment.
21 SECTION 7.51.(c) Applications; Criteria and Guidelines. – No later than August 1
22 of each year that funds are made available for the Program, the Department shall develop and
23 publish criteria and guidelines for the application process for the Program in the upcoming school
24 year, including any documentation required to be submitted by the applicants. The Department
25 shall accept applications until September 30 of each school year. Applications shall include, at a
26 minimum, the following information:
27 (1) Evidence that the applicant has or will be able to establish a relationship with
28 a robotics partner.
29 (2) A proposed budget for the educational and competitive after-school robotics
30 program.
31 SECTION 7.51.(d) Award and Use of Funds. – The Department shall prioritize
32 awarding grants to public school units that participated in the Program in the prior school year.
33 Grant awards shall not exceed fifteen thousand dollars ($15,000) per participating high school in
34 the public school unit. The Department shall award grants to the selected applicants by October
35 31 of each year of the Program. Funds may be used for any of the following purposes:
36 (1) Establishing a relationship with a robotics partner.
37 (2) Purchasing robotics kits.
38 (3) Providing stipends for coaches.
39 (4) Making payments associated with participation in a robotics league or robotics
40 competition.
41 (5) Paying fees incurred as part of the administration of a robotics team.
42 SECTION 7.51.(e) Reporting. – No later than October 15 of each year in which
43 funds are made available for the Program, the Department shall report the following information
44 from the prior school year to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee and the Fiscal
45 Research Division:
46 (1) Number and amounts of grants awarded.
47 (2) Identities of the public school units receiving grants.
