49 NORTHEAST REGIONAL SCHOOL OF BIOTECHNOLOGY AND AGRISCIENCE
50 SECTION 7.55.(a) Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended by adding a
51 new Article to read:
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 153

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "Article 15A.
2 "Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience.
3 "§ 115C-229.5. Purpose.
4 (a) The purpose of this Article is to establish the Northeast Regional School of
5 Biotechnology and Agriscience as a school of choice that will expand student opportunities for
6 educational success through high quality instructional programming in the northeastern region
7 of the State. The Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience may partner with
8 other education partners, including local boards of education, institutions of higher education, or
9 private businesses or organizations, and shall foster, encourage, and promote the development of
10 knowledge and skills in career clusters of critical importance to the region.
11 (b) The Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience is a political
12 subdivision of the State and shall operate as a public school unit with a board of directors as the
13 governing body.
14 (c) Except as otherwise provided in this Article and Article 7B of this Chapter, the
15 Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience is exempt from statutes and rules
16 applicable to a local board of education or local school administrative unit.
17 "§ 115C-229.10. Definitions.
18 The following definitions apply in this Part:
19 (1) Regional school. – The Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and
20 Agriscience.
21 (2) Regional school board of directors or board of directors. – The governing
22 board of the Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience.
23 (3) Regional school service area. – The counties of Beaufort, Bertie, Camden,
24 Currituck, Dare, Edenton, Edgecombe, Gates, Halifax, Hertford, Hyde,
25 Martin, Northampton, Pasquotank, Perquimans, Pitt, Tyrrell, and Washington.
26 "§ 115C-229.15. Board of directors; appointment; terms of office.
27 (a) The board of directors of the regional school shall consist of the following members:
28 (1) The Superintendent of Public Instruction shall appoint three members who are
29 either a local board of education member or superintendent of a local school
30 administrative unit in a county where at least five percent (5%) of the students
31 enrolled in the regional school reside.
32 (2) The State Board of Education shall appoint five members as representatives
33 of the business community, upon the recommendation of the North Carolina
34 Economic Developers Association, who reside in a county where at least five
35 percent (5%) of the students enrolled in the regional school reside. At least
36 one of the appointees shall be a resident of the county in which the regional
37 school is located.
38 (3) The Parent Advisory Council established by G.S. 115C-229.20 shall appoint
39 one member to the board of directors from among the Council membership.
40 The seat shall be declared vacant if the child of the appointed parent no longer
41 attends the regional school.
42 (4) Any institution of higher education partner may appoint a representative of
43 the institution of higher education to serve as an ex officio member of the
44 board of directors.
45 (b) Members shall serve four-year terms of office. Appointed members of the board of
46 directors shall be selected for their interest in and commitment to the importance of public
47 education to regional economic development and to the purposes of the regional school.
48 (c) Whenever an appointed member of the board of directors ceases to meet the
49 qualifications for appointment or for any reason other than ill health or service in the interest of
50 the State or nation to be present at three successive regular meetings of the board of directors, his
51 or her place as a member of the board of directors shall be deemed vacant. Any member of the
Page 154 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 board of directors may be removed from office by the appointing authority for misfeasance,
2 malfeasance, or nonfeasance in office. All vacancies shall be filled by the appointing authority
3 for the remainder of the term of office by an individual meeting the qualifications for the vacated
4 seat.
5 "§ 115C-229.20. Parent Advisory Council; purpose; appointments.
6 (a) Purpose. – There shall be a Parent Advisory Council to serve as a resource and provide
7 input to the board of directors as to the operation of the regional school. The board of directors
8 shall consult the Parent Advisory Council when considering changes to the regional school's
9 operations that may significantly impact students attending the regional school.
10 (b) Appointment. – The Superintendent of Public Instruction shall appoint one member
11 from each county where at least five percent (5%) of the students enrolled in the regional school
12 reside to the Parent Advisory Council for a term of four years or until the member's child no
13 longer attends the regional school. Appointees shall be parents or guardians of students attending
14 the regional school and shall, to the extent possible, reflect the demographic composition of the
15 regional school.
16 "§ 115C-229.25. Board of directors; meetings; rules of procedure; officers.
17 (a) The board of directors shall meet at least four times a year and may hold special
18 meetings at any time at the call of the chair or upon petition addressed to the chair by a majority
19 of the members of the board of directors. All meetings of the board of directors shall be subject
20 to the requirements of Article 33C of Chapter 143 of the General Statutes.
21 (b) The board of directors shall elect a chair and a vice-chair from among its members,
22 who shall serve a two-year term.
23 (c) All members of the board of directors shall be voting members except for the chair,
24 who may vote only on matters to break a tie.
25 (d) The board of directors shall determine its own rules of procedure and may delegate
26 to such committees as it may create such of its powers as it deems appropriate.
27 (e) Members of the board of directors shall receive such per diem compensation and
28 necessary travel and subsistence expenses while engaged in the discharge of their official duties
29 as is provided by law for members of State boards and commissions.
30 "§ 115C-229.30. Board of directors; corporate powers.
31 (a) The board of directors of the regional school shall be known and distinguished by the
32 name of "The Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience Board of Directors"
33 and shall continue as a body politic and corporate and by that name shall have perpetual
34 succession and a common seal. It shall be able and capable in law to take, demand, receive, and
35 possess all moneys, goods, and chattels that shall be given for the use of the regional school, and
36 to apply to same according to the will of the donors; and by gift, purchase, or devise to receive,
37 possess, enjoy, and retain forever any and all real and personal estate and funds, of whatsoever
38 kind, nature, or quality the same may be, in special trust and confidence that the same, or the
39 profits thereof, shall be applied to and for the use and purpose of establishing and endowing the
40 regional school, and shall have power to receive donations from any source whatsoever, to be
41 devoted exclusively to the purposes of the maintenance of the regional school, or according to
42 the terms of the donation.
43 (b) The board of directors shall be able and capable in law to bargain, sell, grant, alien,
44 or dispose of and convey and assure to the purchasers any and all such real and personal estate
45 and funds as it may lawfully acquire when the condition of the grant to it or the will of the devisor
46 does not forbid it; and shall be able and capable in law to sue and be sued in all courts whatsoever;
47 and shall have power to open and receive subscriptions; and in general may do all such things as
48 are usually done by bodies corporate and politic, or such as may be necessary for the promotion
49 of learning and virtue.
50 "§ 115C-229.35. Board of directors; powers and duties.
51 The board of directors shall have the following powers and duties:
