7 (2) "School personnel" means any of the following:
8 a. Member of the board of directors.
9 b. Employee of the regional school.
10 c. Independent contractor or employee of an independent contractor of
11 the regional school if the independent contractor carries out duties
12 customarily performed by school personnel, whether paid with federal,
13 State, local, or other funds, who has significant access to students or
14 who has responsibility for the fiscal management of the regional
15 school.
16 (b) The board of directors shall adopt a policy on whether and under what circumstances
17 school personnel shall be required to be checked for a criminal history. The board of directors
18 shall apply its policy uniformly in requiring school personnel to be checked for a criminal history.
19 The board of directors may grant conditional approval of an application while the board of
20 directors is checking a person's criminal history and making a decision based on the results of
21 the check. The board of directors shall not require school personnel to pay for the criminal history
22 record check authorized under this section.
23 (c) The board of directors shall require the person to be checked by the Department of
24 Public Safety (i) to be fingerprinted and to provide any additional information required by the
25 Department of Public Safety to a person designated by the board of directors or to the local sheriff
26 or the municipal police, whichever is more convenient for the person, and (ii) to sign a form
27 consenting to the check of the criminal record and to the use of fingerprints and other identifying
28 information required by the repositories. The board of directors shall consider refusal to consent
29 when making employment decisions and decisions with regard to independent contractors. The
30 fingerprints of the individual shall be forwarded to the State Bureau of Investigation for a search
31 of the State criminal history record file, and the State Bureau of Investigation shall forward a set
32 of fingerprints to the Federal Bureau of Investigation for a national criminal history record check.
33 The Department of Public Safety shall provide to the board of directors the criminal history from
34 the State and National Repositories of Criminal Histories of any school personnel for which the
35 board of directors requires a criminal history record check. The board of directors shall not
36 require school personnel to pay for the fingerprints authorized under this section.
37 (d) The board of directors shall review the criminal history it receives on an individual.
38 The board of directors shall determine whether the results of the review indicate that the
39 individual (i) poses a threat to the physical safety of students or personnel or (ii) has demonstrated
40 that he or she does not have the integrity or honesty to fulfill his or her duties as school personnel
41 and shall use the information when making employment decisions and decisions with regard to
42 independent contractors. The board of directors shall make written findings with regard to how
43 it used the information when making employment decisions and decisions with regard to
44 independent contractors. The board of directors may delegate any of the duties in this subsection
45 to the principal.
46 (e) The board of directors, or the principal if designated by the board of directors, shall
47 provide to the State Board of Education the criminal history it receives on a person who is
48 certificated, certified, or licensed by the State Board of Education. The State Board of Education
49 shall review the criminal history and determine whether the person's certificate or license should
50 be revoked in accordance with State laws and rules regarding revocation.
