26 "§ 115C-229.55. Finance and budget.
27 (a) The board of directors shall have all the rights, duties, and obligations for receipt,
28 accounting, and dispersing of funds for the school, including all the rights, duties, and obligations
29 specified in Article 31 of this Chapter. The board may contract with a local school administrative
30 unit to serve as the finance agent for the board and shall provide reasonable compensation to the
31 local school administrative unit for this service. Upon such agreement, that local school
32 administrative unit shall act as agent for the board in all receipt, accounting, and dispersing
33 functions, but the board shall retain liability for compliance with Article 31 of this Chapter.
34 (b) A regional school may request appropriations directly from a city, as authorized by
35 G.S. 160A-700.
36 (c) With respect to the receipt, deposit, and disbursement of moneys (i) required by law
37 to be deposited with the State Treasurer or (ii) made available for expenditure by warrants drawn
38 on the State Treasurer, regional schools are subject to Article 6A of Chapter 147 of the General
39 Statutes.
40 (d) The State Board of Education shall allocate to the regional school:
41 (1) An amount equal to the average per pupil allocation for average daily
42 membership from the local school administrative unit allotments in which the
43 regional school is located for each child attending the regional school except
44 for the allocation for children with disabilities and for the allocation for
45 children with limited English proficiency.
46 (2) An additional amount for each child attending the regional school who is a
47 child with disabilities. In the event a child with disabilities leaves the regional
48 school and enrolls in a local school administrative unit during the first 60
49 school days in the school year, the regional school shall return a pro rata
50 amount of funds allocated for that child to the State Board, and the State Board
51 shall reallocate those funds to the local school administrative unit in which the
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 161

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 public school is located. In the event a child with disabilities enrolls in a
2 regional school during the first 60 school days in the school year, the State
3 Board shall allocate to the regional school the pro rata amount of additional
4 funds for children with disabilities.
5 (3) An additional amount for children with limited English proficiency attending
6 the regional school, based on a formula adopted by the State Board.
7 (4) An additional amount equal to the average per pupil share of the local current
8 expense fund of all of the local school administrative units in the regional
9 school service area for the prior fiscal year."
