24 HIGH-INTENSITY TUTORING PROGRAM
25 SECTION 7.56. No later than April 1, 2026, Union County Public Schools, with
26 assistance from the Department of Public Instruction, shall report to the Joint Legislative
27 Education Oversight Committee on Union County Public Schools' high-intensity tutoring
28 program. At a minimum, the report shall include the following:
29 (1) A detailed description of the tutoring plan, including the number of students
30 that participate in each tutoring session and the frequency of tutoring sessions.
31 (2) An overview of the cost of the high-intensity tutoring program, including
32 identifying all funding sources.
33 (3) A detailed description on the impacts of the high-intensity tutoring program
34 on student performance.
35 (4) Lessons Union County Public Schools has learned or challenges overcome in
36 developing the high-intensity tutoring program.
37 (5) Recommendations on how the high-intensity tutoring program could be
38 replicated in other districts.
39 (6) Any other information Union County Public Schools or the Department deems
40 relevant related to high-intensity tutoring programs.
