43 SECTION 7.57. G.S. 115C-375.3 reads as rewritten:
44 "§ 115C-375.3. Guidelines to support and assist students with diabetes.
45 (a) Local boards of education and boards of directors of charter schools Governing bodies
46 of public school units shall ensure that the guidelines adopted by the State Board of Education
47 under G.S. 115C-12(31) are implemented in schools in which students with diabetes are enrolled.
48 In particular, the boards shall require the implementation of the procedures set forth in those
49 guidelines for the development and implementation of individual diabetes care plans. The boards
50 also shall make available necessary information and staff development to teachers and school
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 163

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 personnel in order to appropriately support and assist students with diabetes in accordance with
2 their individual diabetes care plans.
3 (b) Governing bodies of public school units shall ensure that each school provides parents
4 and legal guardians with information about type 1 and type 2 diabetes at the beginning of every
5 school year. This information shall include all of the following:
6 (1) A description of type 1 and type 2 diabetes.
7 (2) A description of the risk factors and warning signs associated with type 1 and
8 type 2 diabetes.
9 (3) A recommendation that if a student is displaying warning signs associated
10 with diabetes, the parent or guardian of the student consult with the primary
11 care provider of the student to determine if immediate screening for diabetes
12 is appropriate.
13 (4) A description of the screening process for and stages of diabetes.
14 (5) A recommendation that if a student receives a diabetes diagnosis, the parent
15 or guardian of the student consult with the primary care provider of the student
16 to develop an appropriate treatment plan.
17 (6) Notification that the school is required to assist students with diabetes in
18 accordance with the rules adopted by the State Board of Education pursuant
19 to G.S. 115C-12(31)."
