22 SECTION 7.58.(a) G.S. 115C-12 is amended by adding the following new
23 subdivisions to read:
24 "(50) Medical Condition Action Plan. – The State Board of Education shall adopt a
25 rule establishing a medical condition action plan as provided in
26 G.S. 115C-375.1 to be implemented by each public school unit for each
27 student at risk for a medical emergency as diagnosed by a doctor.
28 (51) Medical Emergency Plan. – The State Board of Education, in consultation
29 with the Department of Public Instruction and the Department of Health and
30 Human Services, shall adopt a rule establishing the required response of
31 public school unit employees when a student has a medical emergency not
32 otherwise covered by a medical condition action plan implemented in
33 accordance with G.S. 115C-375.1. The Department of Public Instruction shall
34 provide each public school unit with a copy of the rule, and each public school
35 unit shall implement the rule."
36 SECTION 7.58.(b) G.S. 115C-375.1 reads as rewritten:
37 "§ 115C-375.1. To provide some medical care to students.students and implement medical
38 condition action plans.
39 (a) Notwithstanding G.S. 90-21.10B, it is within the scope of duty of teachers, including
40 substitute teachers, teacher assistants, student teachers, or any other public school employee
41 when authorized by the board of education governing body of a public school unit or its designee,
42 (i) to administer any drugs or medication prescribed by a doctor upon written request of the
43 parents, or as described in the medical condition action plan required by subsection (b) of this
44 section, (ii) to give emergency health care when reasonably apparent circumstances indicate that
45 any delay would seriously worsen the physical condition or endanger the life of the pupil, student,
46 and (iii) to perform any other first aid or lifesaving techniques in which the employee has been
47 trained in a program approved by the State Board of Education. At least one public school unit
48 employee per school shall be trained in first aid and lifesaving techniques, including seizure
49 recognition. No public school unit employee, however, other than a school administrator, shall
50 be required to administer drugs or medication or attend lifesaving techniques programs.
