27 SCHOOL PLANNING SECTION DATA SHARING PLATFORM
28 SECTION 7.66.(a) Notwithstanding any provision of this act or the Committee
29 Report described in Section 45.2 of this act to the contrary, the funds appropriated in this act to
30 the Department of Public Instruction shall be increased by the sum of five hundred thousand
31 dollars ($500,000) in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to be allocated to the
32 School Planning Section to contract with a third-party entity to maintain a digital platform to
33 facilitate data sharing among local school administrative units and county governments regarding
34 products and services purchased for elementary and secondary education, including capital
35 improvement projects. In order to promote equitable purchasing in the State, all local school
36 administrative units and county governments shall participate in the platform and share relevant
37 information regarding educational expenses. The platform shall include at least the following
38 components:
39 (1) A consolidated information database regarding all of the following
40 education-related expenses:
41 a. Status and details of expected, proposed, and issued local bonds.
42 b. Interactive listings, ratings, reviews, and contract costs of vendors
43 providing products and services, including, but not limited to, heating,
44 ventilation, and air conditioning and other services related to the
45 maintenance of public school buildings.
46 c. Document-sharing functionality related to purchased products and
47 services, including capital improvement projects.
48 (2) The ability to advertise nationwide requests for proposals from local school
49 administrative units and county governments for education-related products
50 and services, including capital improvement projects.
