26 SECTION 7A.1.(b) Salary Supplements for Teachers Paid on These Salary
27 Schedules. –
28 (1) Licensed teachers who have NBPTS certification shall receive a salary
29 supplement each month of twelve percent (12%) of their monthly salary on
30 the "A" salary schedule.
31 (2) Licensed teachers who are classified as "M" teachers shall receive a salary
32 supplement each month of ten percent (10%) of their monthly salary on the
33 "A" salary schedule.
34 (3) Licensed teachers with licensure based on academic preparation at the
35 six-year degree level shall receive a salary supplement of one hundred
36 twenty-six dollars ($126.00) per month in addition to the supplement provided
37 to them as "M" teachers.
38 (4) Licensed teachers with licensure based on academic preparation at the
39 doctoral degree level shall receive a salary supplement of two hundred
40 fifty-three dollars ($253.00) per month in addition to the supplement provided
41 to them as "M" teachers.
42 (5) Certified school nurses shall receive a salary supplement each month of ten
43 percent (10%) of their monthly salary on the "A" salary schedule.
44 (6) School counselors who are licensed as counselors at the master's degree level
45 or higher shall receive a salary supplement each month of one hundred dollars
46 ($100.00).
