6 SECTION 7A.5. Article 19 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended by
7 adding the following new section to read:
8 "§ 115C-285.5. Bonuses for principals.
9 (a) To the extent funds are made available for this purpose, the Department of Public
10 Instruction shall administer a bonus in each fiscal year to any principal who supervised a school
11 as a principal for a majority of the previous school year if that school was in the top fifty percent
12 (50%) of school growth in the State during the previous school year, calculated by the State
13 Board pursuant to G.S. 115C-83.15(c), as follows:
14 Principal Bonus Schedule
15 Statewide Growth Percentage Bonus
16 Top 5% $15,000
17 Top 10% $10,000
18 Top 15% $5,000
19 Top 20% $2,500
20 Top 50% $1,000
21 A principal shall receive no more than one bonus pursuant to this section. The bonus shall be
22 paid at the highest amount for which the principal qualifies.
23 (b) The bonus awarded pursuant to this section shall be in addition to any regular wage
24 or other bonus the principal receives or is scheduled to receive.
25 (c) Notwithstanding G.S. 135-1(7a), the bonuses awarded pursuant to this section are not
26 compensation under Article 1 of Chapter 135 of the General Statutes, Retirement System for
27 Teachers and State Employees.
28 (d) It is the intent of the General Assembly that funds provided pursuant to this section
29 will supplement principal compensation and not supplant local funds.
30 (e) The bonus provided pursuant to this section shall be paid no later than October 31 of
31 each year to qualifying principals employed as of October 1 of that year."
