33 ASSISTANT PRINCIPAL SALARIES
34 SECTION 7A.6.(a) For each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium, beginning July
35 1, 2025, assistant principals shall receive a monthly salary based on the salary schedule for
36 teachers who are classified as "A" teachers plus nineteen percent (19%). An assistant principal
37 shall be placed on the step on the salary schedule that reflects the total number of years of
38 experience as a certified employee of the public schools. For purposes of this section, an
39 administrator with a one-year provisional assistant principal's certificate shall be considered
40 equivalent to an assistant principal.
41 SECTION 7A.6.(b) Assistant principals with certification based on academic
42 preparation at the six-year degree level shall be paid a salary supplement of one hundred
43 twenty-six dollars ($126.00) per month and at the doctoral degree level shall be paid a salary
44 supplement of two hundred fifty-three dollars ($253.00) per month.
45 SECTION 7A.6.(c) Participants in an approved full-time master's in school
46 administration program shall receive up to a 10-month stipend during the internship period of the
47 master's program. The stipend shall be at the beginning salary of an assistant principal or, for a
48 teacher who becomes an intern, at least as much as that person would earn as a teacher on the
49 teacher salary schedule. The North Carolina Principal Fellows Program or the school of education
50 where the intern participates in a full-time master's in school administration program shall supply
51 the Department of Public Instruction with certification of eligible full-time interns.
