13 AUTHORIZE THE NORTH CAROLINA COLLABORATORY TO STUDY THE
14 INCLUSION OF THE CLASSIC LEARNING TEST AMONG STANDARDIZED
15 TESTS CONSIDERED FOR UNDERGRADUATE ADMISSION AND THE AWARD
16 OF SCHOLARSHIPS AT CONSTITUENT INSTITUTIONS OF THE UNIVERSITY
17 OF NORTH CAROLINA
18 SECTION 8.30.(a) The North Carolina Collaboratory shall study the viability of
19 including Classic Learning Test scores as a part of an application for admission or award of
20 scholarship to a constituent institution of The University of North Carolina. In conducting this
21 study, the Collaboratory shall seek input from The University of North Carolina and the James
22 G. Martin Center for Academic Renewal. As a part of the study, the Collaboratory shall
23 determine:
24 (1) Whether an applicant's score on the Classic Learning Test serves the purpose
25 of aiding constituent institutions in determining (i) an applicant's
26 qualifications for undergraduate admission and (ii) an applicant's
27 qualifications for award of scholarships funded in whole or in part with State
28 funds and administered by an entity of The University of North Carolina.
29 (2) Whether an applicant's performance on the Classic Learning Test is predictive
30 of college success.
31 (3) Whether a score on the Classic Learning Test can be deemed concordant with
32 a score on the SAT or ACT such that The University of North Carolina could
33 use an applicant's score on the Classic Learning Test interchangeably with a
34 score on the SAT or ACT for the purposes of setting minimum requirements
35 for admission and awarding scholarships.
36 (4) The financial, operational, and administrative cost to The University of North
37 Carolina and constituent institutions associated with accepting an applicant's
38 score on the Classic Learning Test in addition to accepting an applicant's score
39 on the SAT or ACT.
40 (5) The financial, operational, and administrative cost to the State of adding the
41 CLT10 to the list of standardized tests offered one time and at no cost to the
42 student for every student in the eighth through tenth grades who has completed
43 Algebra I or who is in the last month of Algebra I pursuant to
44 G.S. 115C-174.18.
45 SECTION 8.30.(b) The Collaboratory shall make a final report on its study to the
46 Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee no later than December 15, 2025.
47 SECTION 8.30.(c) This section is effective when it becomes law.
