31 North Carolina in the next academic year after graduation. The Authority shall
32 have the discretion to postpone this requirement for up to one academic year
33 after graduation if the student is able to demonstrate that any of the following
34 have substantially disrupted or interrupted the student's ability to enroll as a
35 full-time student:
36 a. A military service obligation.
37 b. Serious medical debilitation.
38 c. A short-term or long-term disability.
39 d. Other extraordinary hardship.
40 (3) Submits a completed Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA)
41 form.
42 (b) Students who receive initial tuition grants as a cohort of a high school graduating class
43 of NCSSM or UNCSA shall also be eligible to apply for tuition grants for subsequent academic
44 terms for up to a total of eight academic terms, provided that tuition grants are only used for
45 undergraduate tuition.
46 (b1) A student An eligible student must be continuously enrolled full time in an
47 undergraduate program at a constituent institution of The University of North Carolina after the
48 award of the initial tuition grant to be eligible for tuition grants in subsequent academic terms.
49 The Authority shall have the discretion to waive this requirement if the student is able to
50 demonstrate that any of the following have substantially disrupted or interrupted the student's
51 pursuit of a degree:
