6 as provided in G.S. 116-209.91.
7 "§ 116-209.91. Administration of tuition grants.
8 (a) The Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, the Authority shall administer
9 the tuition grants provided for in this Part pursuant to guidelines and procedures established by
10 the Authority consistent with its practices for administering State-funded financial aid. The
11 guidelines and procedures shall include an application process and schedule, notification and
12 disbursement procedures, standards for reporting, and standards for return of tuition grants when
13 a student withdraws. The Authority shall also require students to submit (i) a completed Free
14 Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) form or (ii) other documentation, as necessary, to
15 administer and award the tuition grant. The Authority shall not approve any grant until it receives
16 proper certification from the appropriate constituent institution that the student applying for the
17 grant is an eligible student. Upon receipt of the certification, the Authority shall remit, at the
18 times it prescribes, the tuition grant to the constituent institution on behalf, and to the credit, of
19 the eligible student. In the event a student on whose behalf a tuition grant has been paid is not
20 enrolled in an undergraduate program and carrying a minimum academic load as of the tenth
21 classroom day following the beginning of the school term for which the tuition grant was paid,
22 the constituent institution shall refund the full amount of the tuition grant to the Authority.
23 (b) Except as otherwise provided in this section, the amount of the grant awarded to a an
24 eligible student under the Program shall cover the tuition cost at the constituent institution in
25 which the eligible student is enrolled. No tuition grant awarded to a an eligible student under this
26 section shall exceed the cost of attendance at a constituent institution for which the eligible
27 student is enrolled.
28 (c) If a student, who is eligible for a tuition grant under this section, an eligible student
29 also receives a scholarship or other grant covering the cost of attendance at the constituent
30 institution for which the tuition grant is awarded, then the amount of the tuition grant shall be
31 reduced by an appropriate amount determined by the Authority so that the total amount of
32 scholarships and grants received by the eligible student does not exceed the cost of attendance
33 for the institution. The cost of attendance shall be determined by the Authority for each
34 constituent institution.
35 (c1) The Authority shall place all funds appropriated to, or otherwise received by, the
36 Authority for the award of tuition grants under this Part into an institutional trust fund established
37 in accordance with the provisions of G.S. 116-36.1. All interest earned on these funds shall also
38 be placed in the institutional trust fund established pursuant to this subsection. The monies in the
39 institutional trust fund may be used only for the purposes set forth in this Part.
40 (d) In the event there are not sufficient funds to provide each eligible student who has
41 applied in accordance with the application process and the schedule established by the Authority
42 with a full tuition grant as provided by this Part, each eligible student shall receive a pro rata
43 share of funds available for the academic term covered by the appropriation in the preceding
44 fiscal year.
45 (e) The Authority may use up to five percent (5%) of the funds appropriated each year
46 for tuition grants under this Part for the administrative costs.costs of the Program."
