7 SECTION 8A.5.(a) Part 2A of Article 39 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes
8 is amended by adding a new section to read:
9 "§ 115C-562.2A. Residency required; qualified exemption for military families.
10 (a) Definitions. – For purposes of this section, the following definitions shall apply:
11 (1) Documentation of military orders. – A copy of the official military order
12 transferring to a military installation or reservation located in the State.
13 (2) Military-connected student. – An eligible student who is the child of a military
14 family, as defined in G.S. 115C-407.5.
15 (b) Residency Required. – Except as otherwise provided in this section, a student shall
16 be a resident of North Carolina that is eligible to attend a North Carolina public school pursuant
17 to Article 25 of this Chapter in both of the following circumstances:
18 (1) At the time the student applies to receive a scholarship grant under this Part.
19 (2) At the beginning of each school year in which the student is eligible to receive
20 scholarship grant funds.
21 (c) Qualified Residency Exemptions for Military-Connected Students. – A
22 military-connected student who is not a resident solely because of military orders impacting the
23 residency of that student and who provides applicable documentation of military orders shall
24 receive the following qualified exemptions related to the residency requirements in this section:
25 (1) If the military-connected student is not a resident during the application period
26 established by the Authority, the Authority shall nevertheless accept the
27 application and award a scholarship grant in accordance with this Part.
28 (2) If the military-connected student is not a resident upon initial enrollment in a
29 nonpublic school, the military-connected student may nevertheless receive
30 grant funds in the first semester of the school year. Thereafter, the student
31 shall not receive a scholarship award until proof of residency is provided in
32 accordance with the requirements of the Authority.
33 (d) Funds and Reports. – Notwithstanding G.S. 115C-562.8, if the funds required to
34 award scholarship grants for military-connected students pursuant to subdivision (c)(1) of this
35 section exceed the funds available for the distribution of those awards, the Authority may allocate
36 the necessary funds from the unencumbered cash balance in the Opportunity Scholarship Grant
37 Fund Reserve. If the Authority expends funds in excess of those available in the Reserve, the
38 Authority shall submit the report required in G.S. 115C-562.7(d) as it relates to the awards
39 provided under this section."
40 SECTION 8A.5.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies
41 beginning with applications for the award of scholarship grants in the 2025-2026 school year.
