42 SECTION 8A.6.(d) Article 23 of Chapter 116 of the General Statutes is amended
43 by adding the following new Part to read:
44 "Part 8. Children of Wartime Veterans Scholarship.
45 "§ 116-209.110. Purpose.
46 In appreciation for the service and sacrifices of North Carolina's war veterans and as evidence
47 of this State's concern for their children, there is established the Children of Wartime Veterans
48 Scholarship Program to be administered by the State Education Assistance Authority. The
49 General Assembly finds that the establishment of the Program is necessary to provide financial
50 assistance from the State to address the unique needs and challenges of the children of wartime
51 veterans to ensure they have opportunities to reach their higher education attainment goals.
Page 212 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "§ 116-209.112. Definitions.
2 The following definitions shall apply in this Part:
3 (1) Active federal service. – One of the following:
4 a. Full-time duty in the Armed Forces other than active duty for training.
5 b. Active duty for training, if disability or death occurs (i) as a direct
6 result of armed conflict or (ii) while engaged in extra-hazardous
7 service, including such service under conditions simulating war.
8 (2) Armed Forces. – The United States Army, Navy, Marine Corps, Air Force,
9 Space Force, and Coast Guard, including their reserve components.
10 (3) Authority. – The State Education Assistance Authority established pursuant
11 to this Article.
12 (4) Disability. – A disability of a veteran that qualifies the veteran to receive
13 compensation under 38 U.S.C. § 101.
14 (5) Eligible child. – A person who meets all of the following criteria:
15 a. Is under 25 years of age at the time of application for a scholarship.
16 b. Qualifies as a resident for tuition purposes under the criteria set forth
17 in G.S. 116-143.1 and in accordance with the coordinated and
18 centralized residency determination process administered by the
19 Authority.
20 c. Holds a high school diploma or its equivalent.
21 d. Is the child of a veteran who meets one of the following criteria:
22 1. Is a resident of North Carolina at the time of completion of the
23 application documentation for the Program.
24 2. Was a resident of North Carolina at the time of entrance into
25 service in the Armed Forces.
26 3. Was permanently stationed in North Carolina at the time of his
27 or her death.
28 4. Is an active duty service member permanently stationed in
29 North Carolina at the time of completion of the application
30 documentation for the Program.
31 e. Submits a completed Free Application for Federal Student Aid
32 (FAFSA) to the Authority.
33 (6) Eligible institution. – A State educational institution or a private educational
34 institution.
35 (7) Period of war or wartime. – Any of the periods or circumstances described
36 below:
37 a. Any period of war as defined in 38 U.S.C. § 101.
38 b. Any period of service in the Armed Forces during which the veteran
39 parent of an applicant for a scholarship under this Part suffered death
40 or disability (i) as a direct result of armed conflict or (ii) while engaged
41 in extra-hazardous service, including such service under conditions
42 simulating war.
43 (8) Private educational institution. – An eligible private postsecondary institution
44 as defined in G.S. 116-280(3).
45 (9) Program. – The Children of Wartime Veterans Scholarship Program
46 established by this Part.
47 (10) State educational institution. – Any constituent institution of The University
48 of North Carolina, or any community college operated under the provisions of
49 Chapter 115D of the General Statutes of North Carolina.
50 (11) Veteran. – Either of the following:
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 213

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 a. A person who served as a member of the Armed Forces in active
2 federal service during a period of war and who was either separated
3 from the Armed Forces under honorable conditions or who is currently
4 serving in a second or subsequent enlistment.
5 b. A person who was separated from the Armed Forces under honorable
6 conditions and whose death or disability was incurred (i) as a direct
