31 NURSING FELLOWS PILOT PROGRAM AT WINSTON-SALEM STATE
32 UNIVERSITY
33 SECTION 8A.10.(a) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
34 (1) Academic term. – A semester or summer session.
35 (2) Authority. – The State Education Assistance Authority.
36 (3) Dean. – The Dean of the School of Health Sciences at WSSU.
37 (4) Eligible nurse. – A nurse who meets all of the following criteria:
38 a. Enrolled at WSSU beginning in the 2026-2027 or 2027-2028
39 academic year.
40 b. Received a forgivable loan under the Program.
41 c. Graduated within 10 years from at least one of the following at WSSU,
42 excluding any authorized deferment for extenuating circumstances:
43 1. A Bachelor of Science in Nursing program.
44 2. A Master of Science in Nursing Education program.
45 d. Is licensed as a registered nurse in this State.
46 (5) Forgivable loan. – A forgivable loan made under the Program.
47 (6) Program. – The Nursing Fellows Pilot Program.
48 (7) Qualifying nurse. – An eligible nurse who meets all of the following criteria:
49 a. Holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing from WSSU.
50 b. Is employed as a nurse in this State.
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 221

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (8) Qualifying nurse instructor. – An eligible nurse who meets all of the following
2 criteria:
3 a. Holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing from WSSU and a
4 Master of Science degree in Nursing Education from WSSU.
5 b. Is employed as an instructor in a qualifying nursing program.
6 (9) Qualifying nursing program. – A nursing program at one of the following that
7 prepares students to earn a degree in nursing and become a licensed practical
8 nurse as defined in Article 9A of Chapter 90 of the General Statutes:
9 a. A community college.
10 b. A university or private postsecondary institution.
11 (10) Trust Fund. – The Nursing Fellows Program Trust Fund.
12 (11) University or private postsecondary institution. – Either of the following:
13 a. A postsecondary constituent institution of The University of North
14 Carolina as defined in G.S. 116-2(4).
15 b. An eligible private postsecondary educational institution as defined in
16 G.S. 116-280(3).
17 (12) WSSU. – Winston-Salem State University.
18 SECTION 8A.10.(b) Program. – There is established the Nursing Fellows Pilot
19 Program. The purpose of the Program is to recruit, prepare, and support eligible nursing students
20 enrolling at WSSU beginning in the 2026-2027 and 2027-2028 academic years for preparation
21 as highly effective nurses and instructors in qualifying nursing programs. The Program shall be
22 used to provide forgivable loans to nursing students who are (i) enrolled in degree programs at
23 WSSU to receive a Bachelor of Science in Nursing or a Master of Science in Nursing Education
24 and (ii) interested in preparing to become nurses in the State or instructors in qualifying nursing
25 programs.
26 SECTION 8A.10.(c) Program Administration; Dean. – The Authority shall
27 administer the Program in cooperation with the Dean. The Dean shall determine forgivable loan
28 recipient selection criteria and selection procedures and shall select the recipients to receive
29 forgivable loans under the Program in accordance with the requirements of this section. The Dean
30 shall appoint any needed staff of the Program and shall be responsible for recruitment and
31 coordination of the Program, including proactive, aggressive, and strategic recruitment of
32 potential recipients. Recruitment activities shall include (i) targeting regions of the State with the
33 greatest need for nurses and nursing instructors in qualifying nursing programs, (ii) actively
34 engaging with registered nurses, business leaders, experts in human resources, elected officials,
35 and other community leaders throughout the State, and (iii) attracting candidates to the Program.
36 WSSU shall provide office space and clerical support staff, as necessary, to the Dean for the
37 Program.
38 SECTION 8A.10.(d) Trust Fund. – There is established the Nursing Fellows
39 Program Trust Fund to be administered by the Authority, in conjunction with the Dean. All funds
40 (i) appropriated to, or otherwise received by, the Program for forgivable loans and other Program
41 purposes, (ii) received as repayment of forgivable loans, and (iii) earned as interest on these funds
42 shall be placed in the Trust Fund. The purpose of the Trust Fund is to provide financial assistance
43 to qualified students to fill needed positions for nurses in the State and instructors in qualifying
44 nursing programs through completion of a Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing or both a
45 Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing and a Master of Science degree in Nursing Education.
46 SECTION 8A.10.(e) Uses of Monies in the Trust Fund. – The monies in the Trust
47 Fund may be used only for forgivable loans granted under the Program, administrative costs
48 associated with the Program, including recruitment and recovery of funds advanced under the
49 Program, mentoring and coaching support to forgivable loan recipients, and extracurricular
50 enhancement activities of the Program in accordance with the following:
Page 222 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) The Authority shall transfer six percent (6%) of the available funds from the
2 Trust Fund to WSSU at the beginning of each fiscal year for the following
3 purposes:
4 a. The Program's administrative costs.
5 b. Extracurricular enhancement activities of the Program.
6 c. Mentoring and coaching support to forgivable loan recipients.
7 (2) The Authority may use up to four percent (4%) of the funds appropriated to
8 the Trust Fund each fiscal year for administrative costs associated with the
9 Program.
10 SECTION 8A.10.(f) Student Selection Criteria for Forgivable Loans. – The Dean,
11 in consultation with the Associate Dean of Nursing at WSSU, shall adopt stringent standards for
12 awarding forgivable loans based on multiple measures to ensure that only the strongest applicants
13 receive them, including the following:
14 (1) Grade point averages.
15 (2) Performance on relevant assessments.
16 (3) Experience, accomplishments, and other criteria demonstrating qualities
17 positively correlated with highly effective nurses and instructors in qualifying
18 nursing programs, including excellent verbal and communication skills.
19 (4) Demonstrated commitment to serve in North Carolina.
20 SECTION 8A.10.(g) Awards of Forgivable Loans. – The Program shall provide
21 forgivable loans to selected students who are initially enrolled in a Bachelor of Science in
22 Nursing degree program at WSSU. Loan payments shall be provided each year for completion
23 of the Bachelor of Science in Nursing program and, if a loan recipient seeks to become a
24 qualifying nurse instructor, for a Master of Science in Nursing Education program. The student
25 shall be eligible to receive loan payments for the Master of Science in Nursing Education
26 program as long as the student enrolls within two years of graduation from the Bachelor of
27 Science in Nursing program. Forgivable loans may be used for tuition, fees, the cost of books,
28 and expenses related to completing a Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing and a Master of
29 Science degree in Nursing Education. Forgivable loans shall be awarded per academic term in
30 amounts of up to five thousand dollars ($5,000) per semester or two thousand five hundred dollars
31 ($2,500) per summer session, as follows:
32 (1) For students pursuing careers as qualifying nurses, for up to five semesters.
33 (2) For persons pursuing careers as qualifying nurse instructors, for up to nine
34 semesters.
35 SECTION 8A.10.(h) Administration of Forgivable Loan Awards. – Upon the
36 naming of recipients of the forgivable loans by the Dean, the Dean shall transfer to the Authority
37 its decisions. The Authority, in coordination with the Dean, shall perform all of the administrative
38 functions necessary to implement this section, which functions shall include rulemaking,
39 disseminating information, acting as a liaison with participating institutions of higher education,
40 implementing forgivable loan agreements, loan monitoring, loan canceling through service and
41 collection, determining the acceptability of service repayment agreements, enforcing the
42 agreements, and all other functions necessary for the execution, payment, and enforcement of
43 promissory notes required under this section.
44 SECTION 8A.10.(i) Annual Report. – The Dean, in coordination with the Authority,
45 shall report no later than January 1, 2027, and annually thereafter while forgivable loans are being
46 serviced under the Program, to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee regarding
47 the following:
48 (1) Forgivable loans awarded from the Trust Fund, including the following:
49 a. Demographic information regarding recipients.
50 b. Number of recipients by institution of higher education.
51 (2) Placement and repayment rates, including the following:
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 223

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 a. Number of graduates who have been employed as qualifying nurses in
2 the State and qualifying nurse instructors in qualifying nursing
3 programs within two years of graduation.
4 b. Number of graduates who have elected to do loan repayment and their
5 years of service, if any, prior to beginning loan repayment.
6 c. Graduation rates of associate degree students taught by instructors in
7 qualifying nursing programs who are recipients of loans under the
8 Program.
9 (3) Mentoring and coaching support, including the number of forgivable loan
10 recipients who received mentoring and coaching support.
11 (4) Selected nurse employer outcomes by degree program, including the
12 following:
13 a. Turnover rate for forgivable loan graduates, including the turnover rate
14 for graduates who also received mentoring and coaching support.
15 b. Fulfillment rate of forgivable loan graduates.
16 SECTION 8A.10.(j) Terms of Forgivable Loans. – All forgivable loans shall be
17 evidenced by notes made payable to the Authority that bear interest at a rate not to exceed ten
18 percent (10%) per year as set by the Authority and beginning on the first day of September after
19 completion of the applicable degree program or 90 days after graduation, whichever is later. If a
20 forgivable loan is terminated, the note shall be made payable to the Authority 90 days after
21 termination of the forgivable loan. The forgivable loan may be terminated upon the recipient's
22 withdrawal from the Program or by the recipient's failure to meet the standards set by the Dean.
23 SECTION 8A.10.(k) Forgiveness. – For every year a qualifying nurse remains a
24 qualifying nurse or a qualifying nurse instructor remains a qualifying nurse instructor, the
25 Authority shall forgive one-third of the total loan amount received over the course of enrollment
26 in the applicable degree program and any interest accrued on that amount. The Authority shall
27 also forgive the loan if it finds that it is impossible for the recipient to work for up to three years,
28 within 10 years after completion of the Bachelor of Science in Nursing degree program for
29 persons pursuing forgiveness as qualifying nurses or of the Master of Science in Nursing
30 Education degree program for persons pursuing forgiveness as qualifying nurse instructors,
31 because of the death or permanent disability of the recipient. If the recipient repays the forgivable
32 loan by cash payments, all indebtedness shall be repaid within 10 years after completion of the
33 latest applicable degree program supported by the forgivable loan. If the recipient completes the
34 applicable degree program, payment of principal and interest shall begin no later than the first
35 day of September after the completion of the program. Should a recipient present extenuating
36 circumstances, the Authority may extend the period to repay the loan in cash to no more than a
37 total of 12 years.
38 SECTION 8A.10.(l) Notwithstanding G.S. 116-209.45(h), beginning in the
39 2026-2027 fiscal year, to the extent funds remain available in the Forgivable Education Loans
40 for Service Fund at the end of each fiscal year, the Authority may use those funds to administer
41 the Nursing Fellows Pilot Program in accordance with this section.
42 SECTION 8A.10.(m) The Dean of the School of Health Sciences at Winston-Salem
43 State University shall establish initial selection criteria for recipients no later than November 15,
