34 0 – 5 200%
35 6 – 12 133%
36 The eligibility for any child with special needs, including a child who is 13 years of
37 age or older, shall be two hundred percent (200%) of the federal poverty level.
38 SECTION 9D.3.(b) The fees for families who are required to share in the cost of
39 care are established based on ten percent (10%) of gross family income. Effective August 1,
40 2026, the fees for families who are required to share in the cost of care are established based on
41 seven percent (7%) of gross family income. When care is received at the blended rate, the
42 copayment shall be eighty-three percent (83%) of the full-time copayment. Copayments for
43 part-time care shall be seventy-five percent (75%) of the full-time copayment.
44 SECTION 9D.3.(c) Payments for the purchase of child care services for low-income
45 children shall be in accordance with the following requirements:
46 (1) Religious sponsored child care facilities operating pursuant to G.S. 110-106
47 and licensed child care centers and homes that meet the minimum licensing
48 standards that are participating in the subsidized child care program shall be
