19 CHILD CARE ALLOCATION FORMULA
20 SECTION 9D.4.(a) The Department of Health and Human Services, Division of
21 Child Development and Early Education (Division), shall allocate child care subsidy voucher
22 funds to pay the costs of necessary child care for minor children of needy families. The
23 mandatory thirty percent (30%) North Carolina Partnership for Children, Inc., subsidy allocation
24 under G.S. 143B-168.15(g) shall constitute the base amount for each county's child care subsidy
25 allocation. The Department of Health and Human Services shall use the following method when
26 allocating federal and State child care funds, not including the aggregate mandatory thirty percent
27 (30%) North Carolina Partnership for Children, Inc., subsidy allocation:
28 (1) Funds shall be allocated to a county based upon the projected cost of serving
29 children under age 11 in families with all parents working who earn less than
30 the applicable federal poverty level percentage set forth in Section 9D.3(a) of
31 this act.
32 (2) The Division may withhold up to two percent (2%) of available funds from
33 the allocation formula for (i) preventing termination of services throughout
34 the fiscal year and (ii) repayment of any federal funds identified by counties
35 as overpayments, including overpayments due to fraud. The Division shall
36 allocate to counties any funds withheld before the end of the fiscal year when
37 the Division determines the funds are not needed for the purposes described
38 in this subdivision. The Division shall submit a report to the Joint Legislative
39 Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services and the Fiscal Research
40 Division, which report shall include each of the following:
41 a. The amount of funds used for preventing termination of services and
42 the repayment of any federal funds.
43 b. The date the remaining funds were distributed to counties.
44 c. As a result of funds withheld under this subdivision and after funds
45 have been distributed, any counties that did not receive at least the
46 amount the counties received the previous year and the amount by
47 which funds were decreased.
48 The Division shall submit a report in each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal
49 biennium 30 days after the funds withheld pursuant to this subdivision are
50 distributed but no later than April 1 of each respective year.
