32 EXEMPT CERTAIN DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE FAMILY CHILD CARE HOMES
33 FROM CHILD CARE LICENSURE
34 SECTION 9D.8. Article 7 of Chapter 110 of the General Statutes is amended by
35 adding a new section to read:
36 "§ 110-106.3. Exemption for certain Department of Defense family child care homes from
37 child care licensure requirements.
38 (a) The provisions of this Article shall not apply to a family child care home operating in
39 this State and located outside of the boundaries of a military installation if the family child care
40 home has a certificate issued by the United States Department of Defense (DOD) or the United
41 States Coast Guard to provide child care and has completed background screening by the DOD
42 pursuant to 34 U.S.C. § 20351 and 32 C.F.R. Part 86 and received a favorable suitability and
43 fitness determination. This exemption applies to DOD family child care home operators
44 providing child care exclusively to children eligible for care under the DOD Instruction 6060.02.
45 (b) A family child care home seeking to operate pursuant to this section shall register
46 with the Department. The individual at each military installation who provides oversight of
47 family child care homes shall be responsible for registering the family child care home operating
48 under this section with the Department. The Department shall establish and maintain a registry
49 in accordance with this section and the registry shall be used for the following limited purposes:
50 (1) Ensuring the DOD family child care home is fully compliant with all DOD
51 requirements to operate the family child care home.
