31 dispensing fee shall be set at one hundred percent (100%) of the Medicaid pharmacy
32 fee-for-service reimbursement methodologies in Attachment 4.19-B of section 12 of the
33 Medicaid State Plan under Title XIX of the Social Security Act Medicaid Assistance Program,
34 as filed with, and approved by, the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services. The National
35 Average Drug Acquisition Cost (NADAC), when applicable and as allowed under the Medicaid
36 State Plan, plus a professional dispensing fee based on the cost of the dispensing study conducted
37 on behalf of the North Carolina Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Health
38 Benefits, will serve as the primary method utilized for reimbursement for retail community
39 pharmacy claims not dispensed utilizing covered outpatient drugs acquired through the 340B
40 drug discount program established under 42 U.S.C. § 256b. All claims utilizing drugs acquired
41 through the 340B drug discount program shall be reimbursed in accordance with the
42 CMS-approved Medicaid State Plan.
43 "SECTION 9D.19A.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and expires June 30,
44 2026.2031."
