11 SECTION 9E.16.(o) G.S. 108A-147.5 reads as rewritten:
12 "§ 108A-147.5. Presumptive service cost component.
13 (a) For every State fiscal quarter prior to the fiscal quarter in which G.S. 108A-54.3A(24)
14 becomes effective, the presumptive service cost component is zero.
15 (b) For the State fiscal quarter in which G.S. 108A-54.3A(24) becomes effective, the
16 presumptive service cost component is the product of forty-eight million seven hundred fifty
17 thousand dollars ($48,750,000) multiplied by the number of months in that State fiscal quarter in
18 which G.S. 108A-54.3A(24) is effective during any part of the month.
19 (c) For the first State fiscal quarter after the State fiscal quarter in which
20 G.S. 108A-54.3A(24) becomes effective, the presumptive service cost component is one hundred
21 forty-six million two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($146,250,000).
22 (d) For the second State fiscal quarter after the State fiscal quarter in which
23 G.S. 108A-54.3A(24) becomes effective, and for each State fiscal quarter thereafter, the
24 presumptive service cost component is an amount of money that is the greatest of the following:
25 (1) The prior quarter's presumptive service cost component amount.
26 (2) The prior quarter's presumptive service cost component amount increased by
27 a percentage that is the sum of each monthly percentage change in the
28 Consumer Price Index: Medical Care for the most recent three months
29 available on the first day of the current quarter.
30 (3) The prior quarter's presumptive service cost component amount increased by
31 the percentage change in the weighted average of the base capitation rates for
32 standard benefit plans for all rating groups associated with newly eligible
33 individuals compared to the prior quarter. The weight for each rating group
34 shall be calculated using member months documented in the Medicaid
35 managed care capitation rate certification for standard benefit plans.
36 (4) The prior quarter's presumptive service cost component amount increased by
37 the percentage change in the weighted average of the base capitation rates for
38 BH IDD tailored plans for all rating groups associated with newly eligible
39 individuals compared to the prior quarter. The weight for each rating group
40 shall be calculated using member months documented in the Medicaid
41 managed care capitation rate certification for BH IDD tailored plans.
42 (5) The amount produced from multiplying 1.15 by the highest amount produced
43 when calculating, for each quarter that is at least two and not more than five
44 quarters prior to the current quarter, the actual nonfederal expenditures for the
45 applicable quarter minus the HASP health advancement acute care hospital
46 HASP component calculated under G.S. 108A-147.6 for the applicable
47 quarter and minus the health advancement freestanding psychiatric hospital
48 HASP component calculated under G.S. 108A-147.6A for the applicable
49 quarter."
