Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 259

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (2) Conduct an actuarial evaluation of the current healthcare spend on primary
2 care services, both as it relates to the NC Medicaid program and the
3 commercial market, including Medicare Advantage plans.
4 (3) Determine the adequacy of the primary care delivery system in North
5 Carolina, including the impact this system has on the supply of the primary
6 care providers in this State.
7 (4) Study the primary care payment landscape in other states, specifically
8 considering states that have implemented a minimum primary care spend.
