49 SINGLE-STREAM FUNDING FOR DMH/DD/SUS COMMUNITY SERVICES
50 SECTION 9G.1.(a) For the purpose of mitigating cash flow problems that many
51 local management entities/managed care organizations (LME/MCOs) experience at the
Page 268 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 beginning of each fiscal year relative to single-stream funding, the Department of Health and
2 Human Services, Division of Mental Health, Developmental Disabilities, and Substance Use
3 Services (DMH/DD/SUS), shall distribute not less than one-twelfth of each LME/MCO's base
4 budget allocation at the beginning of the fiscal year and subtract the amount of that distribution
5 from the LME/MCO's total reimbursements for the fiscal year. For each month of the fiscal year
6 after July, DMH/DD/SUS shall distribute, on the third working day of the month, one-eleventh
7 of the amount of each LME/MCO's single-stream allocation that remains after subtracting the
8 amount of the distribution that was made to the LME/MCO in July of the fiscal year.
9 SECTION 9G.1.(c) During each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium, each
10 LME/MCO shall offer at least the same level of service utilization as during the 2024-2025 fiscal
11 year across the LME/MCO's catchment area. This requirement shall not be construed to require
12 LME/MCOs to authorize or maintain the same level of services for any specific individual whose
13 services were paid for with single-stream funding. Further, this requirement shall not be
14 construed to create a private right of action for any person or entity against the State of North
15 Carolina or the Department of Health and Human Services or any of its divisions, agents, or
16 contractors and shall not be used as authority in any contested case brought pursuant to Chapter
17 108C or 108D of the General Statutes.
18 SECTION 9G.1.(d) If, on or after June 1, 2025, the Office of State Budget and
19 Management (OSBM) certifies a Medicaid budget surplus and sufficient cash in Budget Code
20 14445 to meet total obligations for the 2024-2025 fiscal year, then DHB shall transfer to
21 DMH/DD/SUS funds not to exceed the amount of the certified surplus or thirty million dollars
22 ($30,000,000), whichever is less, to be used for single-stream funding.
23 SECTION 9G.1.(e) If, on or after June 1, 2026, the Office of State Budget and
24 Management (OSBM) certifies a Medicaid budget surplus and sufficient cash in Budget Code
25 14445 to meet total obligations for the 2025-2026 fiscal year, then DHB shall transfer to
26 DMH/DD/SUS funds not to exceed the amount of the certified surplus or thirty million dollars
27 ($30,000,000), whichever is less, to be used for single-stream funding.
