50 LOCAL INPATIENT PSYCHIATRIC BEDS OR BED DAYS
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 269

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 SECTION 9G.3.(a) Use of Funds. – Funds appropriated in this act to the Department
2 of Health and Human Services, Division of Mental Health, Developmental Disabilities, and
3 Substance Use Services, shall continue to be used for the purchase of local inpatient psychiatric
4 beds or bed days. The Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS) shall continue to
5 implement a two-tiered system of payment for purchasing these local inpatient psychiatric beds
6 or bed days based on acuity level with an enhanced rate of payment for inpatient psychiatric beds
7 or bed days for individuals with higher acuity levels, as defined by DHHS. The enhanced rate of
8 payment for inpatient psychiatric beds or bed days for individuals with higher acuity levels shall
9 not exceed the lowest average cost per patient bed day among the State psychiatric hospitals. In
10 addition, at the discretion of the Secretary of Health and Human Services, existing funds allocated
11 to LME/MCOs for community-based mental health, developmental disabilities, and substance
12 use disorder services may be used to purchase additional local inpatient psychiatric beds or bed
13 days. DHHS may allocate funding to the LME/MCOs for the purchase of facility-based crisis,
14 nonhospital detoxification services, and peer respite services to support individuals that do not
15 meet the medical necessity for inpatient treatment and can be diverted from an inpatient hospital
16 stay.
17 SECTION 9G.3.(b) Distribution and Management of Beds or Bed Days. – DHHS
18 shall work to ensure that any local inpatient psychiatric beds or bed days purchased in accordance
19 with this section are utilized solely for individuals who are medically indigent, except that DHHS
20 may use up to forty percent (40%) of the funds appropriated in this act to the Department of
21 Health and Human Services, Division of Mental Health, Developmental Disabilities, and
22 Substance Use Services, for the purchase of local inpatient psychiatric beds or bed days to pay
23 for facility-based crisis services, nonhospital detoxification services, and peer respite services for
24 individuals in need of these services, regardless of whether the individuals are medically indigent.
25 For the purposes of this subsection, "medically indigent" shall mean uninsured persons who (i)
26 are financially unable to obtain private insurance coverage, as determined by DHHS, and (ii) are
27 not eligible for government-funded health coverage such as Medicare or Medicaid.
28 In addition, DHHS shall work to ensure that any local inpatient psychiatric beds or
29 bed days purchased in accordance with this section are distributed across the State and according
30 to need, as determined by DHHS. DHHS shall ensure that beds or bed days for individuals with
31 higher acuity levels are distributed across the State and according to greatest need based on
32 hospital bed utilization data. DHHS shall enter into contracts with LME/MCOs and local
33 hospitals for the purchase and management of the local inpatient psychiatric beds or bed days
34 and allocate up to forty percent (40%) of the total funding to the LME/MCOs for the purpose of
35 facility-based crisis services, nonhospital detoxification services, and peer respite services.
36 DHHS shall work to ensure that these contracts are awarded equitably around all regions of the
37 State. LME/MCOs shall manage and control these local inpatient psychiatric beds or bed days,
38 including the determination of the specific local hospital or State psychiatric hospital to which
39 an individual should be admitted pursuant to an involuntary commitment order.
40 DHHS shall prioritize use of local inpatient psychiatric beds or bed days funded by
41 the Dorothea Dix Hospital Property Fund established under G.S. 143C-9-2(b1).
42 SECTION 9G.3.(c) Funds to be Held in Statewide Reserve. – Funds appropriated in
43 this act to DHHS for the purchase of local inpatient psychiatric beds or bed days shall not be
44 allocated to LME/MCOs but shall be held in a statewide reserve at the Division of Mental Health,
45 Developmental Disabilities, and Substance Use Services to pay for services authorized by the
46 LME/MCOs and billed by the hospitals through the LME/MCOs. LME/MCOs shall remit claims
47 for payment to DHHS within 15 working days after receipt of a clean claim from the hospital
48 and shall pay the hospital within 30 working days after receipt of payment from DHHS.
49 SECTION 9G.3.(d) Ineffective LME/MCO Management of Beds or Bed Days. – If
50 DHHS determines that (i) an LME/MCO is not effectively managing the beds or bed days for
51 which it has responsibility, as evidenced by beds or bed days in the local hospital not being
Page 270 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 utilized while demand for services at the State psychiatric hospitals has not decreased, or (ii) the
2 LME/MCO has failed to comply with the prompt payment provisions of this section, DHHS may
3 contract with another LME/MCO to manage the beds or bed days or, notwithstanding any other
4 provision of law to the contrary, may pay the hospital directly.
5 SECTION 9G.3.(e) Reporting by LME/MCOs. – LME/MCOs shall be required to
6 report to DHHS regarding the utilization of these beds or bed days.
