28 LOCAL HEALTH DEPARTMENTS/COMPETITIVE GRANT PROCESS TO
29 IMPROVE MATERNAL AND CHILD HEALTH
30 SECTION 9H.1.(a) Funds appropriated in this act to the Department of Health and
31 Human Services, Division of Public Health, for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to
32 award competitive grants to local health departments for the improvement of maternal and child
33 health shall be used to continue administering a competitive grant process for local health
34 departments based on maternal and infant health indicators and the county's detailed proposal to
35 invest in evidence-based programs to achieve the following goals:
36 (1) Improve North Carolina's birth outcomes.
37 (2) Improve the overall health status of children in this State from birth to age 5.
38 (3) Lower the State's infant mortality rate.
39 SECTION 9H.1.(b) The plan for administering the competitive grant process shall
40 include at least all of the following components:
41 (1) A request for application (RFA) process to allow local health departments to
42 apply for and receive State funds on a competitive basis. The Department shall
43 require local health departments to include in the application a plan to evaluate
44 the effectiveness, including measurable impact or outcomes, of the activities,
45 services, and programs for which the funds are being requested.
46 (2) A requirement that the Secretary prioritize grant awards to those local health
47 departments that are able to leverage non-State funds in addition to the grant
48 award.
49 (3) Ensures that funds received by the Department to implement the plan
50 supplement and do not supplant existing funds for maternal and child health
51 initiatives.
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 273

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (4) Allows grants to be awarded to local health departments for up to three years.
