42 USE FOSTER CARE BUDGET FOR GUARDIANSHIP ASSISTANCE PROGRAM
43 SECTION 9J.4. Of the funds available for the provision of foster care services, the
44 Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Social Services, may continue to provide
45 for the financial support of children who are deemed to be (i) in a permanent family placement
46 setting, (ii) eligible for legal guardianship, and (iii) otherwise unlikely to receive permanency.
47 No additional expenses shall be incurred beyond the funds budgeted for foster care for the
48 Guardianship Assistance Program (GAP). The Guardianship Assistance Program shall include
49 provisions for extending guardianship services for individuals and youth who exited foster care
50 through the Guardianship Assistance Program after 14 years of age or who have attained the age
51 of 18 years and opt to continue to receive guardianship services until reaching 21 years of age if
