31 SUCCESSFUL TRANSITION/FOSTER CARE YOUTH
32 SECTION 9J.7. The Foster Care Transitional Living Initiative Fund shall continue
33 to fund and support transitional living services that demonstrate positive outcomes for youth,
34 attract significant private sector funding, and lead to the development of evidence-based
35 programs to serve the at-risk population described in this section. The Fund shall continue to
36 support a demonstration project with services provided by Youth Villages to (i) improve
37 outcomes for youth ages 17-21 years who transition from foster care through implementation of
38 outcome-based Transitional Living Services, (ii) identify cost-savings in social services and
39 juvenile and adult correction services associated with the provision of Transitional Living
40 Services to youth aging out of foster care, and (iii) take necessary steps to establish an
41 evidence-based transitional living program available to all youth aging out of foster care. In
42 continuing to implement these goals, the Foster Care Transitional Living Initiative Fund shall
43 support the following strategies:
44 (1) Transitional Living Services, which is an outcome-based program that follows
45 the Youth Villages Transitional Living Model. Outcomes on more than 7,000
46 participants have been tracked since the program's inception. The program has
47 been evaluated through an independent randomized controlled trial. Results
48 indicate that the Youth Villages Transitional Living Model had positive
49 impacts in a variety of areas, including housing stability, earnings, economic
50 hardship, mental health, and intimate partner violence in comparison to the
51 control population.
Page 282 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (2) Public-Private Partnership, which is a commitment by private-sector funding
2 partners to match at least twenty-five percent (25%) of the funds appropriated
3 to the Foster Care Transitional Living Initiative Fund for the 2025-2027 fiscal
4 biennium for the purposes of providing Transitional Living Services through
5 the Youth Villages Transitional Living Model to youth aging out of foster
6 care.
7 (3) Impact Measurement and Evaluation, which are services funded through
8 private partners to provide independent measurement and evaluation of the
9 impact the Youth Villages Transitional Living Model has on the youth served,
10 the foster care system, and on other programs and services provided by the
11 State which are utilized by former foster care youth.
12 (4) Advancement of Evidence-Based Process, which is the implementation and
13 ongoing evaluation of the Youth Villages Transitional Living Model for the
14 purposes of establishing the first evidence-based transitional living program
15 in the nation. To establish the evidence-based program, additional randomized
16 controlled trials may be conducted to advance the model.
