14 GENERAL PROVISIONS
15 SECTION 9M.1.(b) Information to be Included in Block Grant Plans. – The
16 Department of Health and Human Services shall submit a separate plan for each Block Grant
17 received and administered by the Department, and each plan shall include the following:
18 (1) A delineation of the proposed allocations by program or activity, including
19 State and federal match requirements.
20 (2) A delineation of the proposed State and local administrative expenditures.
21 (3) An identification of all new positions to be established through the Block
22 Grant, including permanent, temporary, and time-limited positions.
23 (4) A comparison of the proposed allocations by program or activity with two
24 prior years' program and activity budgets and two prior years' actual program
25 or activity expenditures.
26 (5) A projection of current year expenditures by program or activity.
27 (6) A projection of federal Block Grant funds available, including unspent federal
28 funds from the current and prior fiscal years.
29 (7) The required amount of maintenance of effort and the amount of funds
30 qualifying for maintenance of effort in the previous year delineated by
31 program or activity.
32 SECTION 9M.1.(c) Changes in Federal Fund Availability. – If the Congress of the
33 United States increases the federal fund availability for any of the Block Grants or contingency
34 funds and other grants related to existing Block Grants administered by the Department of Health
35 and Human Services from the amounts appropriated in this act, the Department shall allocate the
36 increase proportionally across the program and activity appropriations identified for that Block
37 Grant in this section. In allocating an increase in federal fund availability, the Office of State
38 Budget and Management shall not approve funding for new programs or activities not
39 appropriated in this act.
40 If the Congress of the United States decreases the federal fund availability for any of
41 the Block Grants or contingency funds and other grants related to existing Block Grants
42 administered by the Department of Health and Human Services from the amounts appropriated
43 in this act, the Department shall develop a plan to adjust the Block Grants based on reduced
44 federal funding.
45 Notwithstanding the provisions of this subsection, for fiscal years 2025-2026 and
46 2026-2027, increases in the federal fund availability for the Temporary Assistance to Needy
47 Families (TANF) Block Grant shall be used only for the North Carolina Child Care Subsidy
48 program to pay for child care and shall not be used to supplant State funds.
49 Prior to allocating the change in federal fund availability, the proposed allocation
50 must be approved by the Office of State Budget and Management. If the Department adjusts the
51 allocation of any Block Grant due to changes in federal fund availability, then a report shall be
Page 294 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 made to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services and the Fiscal
2 Research Division.
3 SECTION 9M.1.(d) Except as otherwise provided, appropriations from federal
4 Block Grant funds are made for each year of the fiscal biennium ending June 30, 2027, according
5 to the schedule enacted for State fiscal years 2025-2026 and 2026-2027, or until a new schedule
6 is enacted by the General Assembly.
7 SECTION 9M.1.(e) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (e1) of this section,
8 all changes to the budgeted allocations to the Block Grants or contingency funds and other grants
9 related to existing Block Grants administered by the Department of Health and Human Services
10 that are not specifically addressed in this section shall be approved by the Office of State Budget
11 and Management. The Office of State Budget and Management shall not approve funding for
12 new programs or activities not appropriated in this section. Additionally, if budgeted allocations
13 are decreased, the Office of State Budget and Management shall not approve any reduction of
14 funds designated for subrecipients in subsection (a) of this section under (i) Item 03 of the
15 Substance Use Prevention, Treatment, and Recovery Services Block Grant or (ii) Item 01 or 02
16 of the Maternal and Child Health Block Grant. The Office of State Budget and Management shall
17 consult with the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services for
18 review prior to implementing any changes. In consulting, the report shall include an itemized
19 listing of affected programs, including associated changes in budgeted allocations. All changes
20 to the budgeted allocations to the Block Grants shall be reported immediately to the Joint
21 Legislative Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services and the Fiscal Research
22 Division. This subsection does not apply to Block Grant changes caused by legislative salary
23 increases and benefit adjustments.
24 SECTION 9M.1.(e1) The Department of Health and Human Services shall have the
25 authority to realign appropriated funds under subsection (a) of this section for Item 01 or 02 in
26 the Maternal and Child Health Block Grant to maintain federal compliance and programmatic
27 alignment, so long as the realignment does not result in a reduction of funds designated for
28 subrecipients under subsection (a) of this section. The Department of Health and Human Services
29 is authorized to realign appropriated funds between the Maternal and Child Health Block Grant
30 categories as provided in this subsection without prior consultation with the Joint Legislative
31 Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services or without exceeding the total amount
32 appropriated for the items.
33 SECTION 9M.1.(f) Except as otherwise provided, the Department of Health and
34 Human Services shall have flexibility to transfer funding between the Temporary Assistance for
35 Needy Families (TANF) Block Grant and the TANF Emergency Contingency Funds Block Grant
36 so long as the total allocation for the line items within those Block Grants remains the same.
