9 SECTION 9M.1.(t) The Division of Social Services shall have the authority to
10 realign appropriated funds between the State-level services Low-Income Energy Assistance
11 Payments and Crisis Assistance Payments without prior consultation with the Joint Legislative
12 Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services to ensure needs are effectively met without
13 exceeding the total amount appropriated for these State-level service items. Additional
14 emergency contingency funds received may be allocated for Energy Assistance Payments or
15 Crisis Intervention Payments without prior consultation with the Joint Legislative Oversight
16 Committee on Health and Human Services. Additional funds received shall be reported to the
17 Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services and the Fiscal Research
18 Division upon notification of the award. The Department of Health and Human Services shall
19 not allocate funds for any activities, including increasing administration, other than assistance
20 payments, without prior consultation with the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Health
21 and Human Services.
22 SECTION 9M.1.(u) The sum of fifty-six million three hundred sixty-nine thousand
23 two hundred eighty-one dollars ($56,369,281) for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium
24 appropriated in this act in the Low-Income Home Energy Assistance Block Grant to the
25 Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Social Services, shall be used for Energy
26 Assistance Payments for the households of (i) elderly persons age 60 and above with income up
27 to one hundred fifty percent (150%) of the federal poverty level and (ii) disabled persons eligible
28 for services funded through the Division of Aging.
29 County departments of social services shall submit to the Division of Social Services
30 an outreach plan for targeting households with 60-year-old household members no later than
31 August 1 of each year. The outreach plan shall comply with the following:
32 (1) Ensure that eligible households are made aware of the available assistance,
33 with particular attention paid to the elderly population age 60 and above and
34 disabled persons receiving services through the Division of Aging.
35 (2) Include efforts by the county department of social services to contact other
36 State and local governmental entities and community-based organizations to
37 (i) offer the opportunity to provide outreach and (ii) receive applications for
38 energy assistance.
39 (3) Be approved by the local board of social services or human services board
40 prior to submission.
