41 "(a) Weekly Benefit Amount. – The weekly benefit amount for an individual who is totally
42 unemployed is an amount equal to the wages paid to the individual in the last two completed
43 quarters of the individual's base period divided by 52 and rounded to the next lower whole dollar.
44 If this amount is less than fifteen dollars ($15.00), the individual is not eligible for benefits. The
45 weekly benefit amount may not exceed three hundred fifty dollars ($350.00).four hundred fifty
46 dollars ($450.00)."
