42 ESTABLISH THE BRUSHY MOUNTAIN STATE NATURAL AREA
43 SECTION 14.8.(a) The General Assembly authorizes the Department of Natural and
44 Cultural Resources to create the Brushy Mountain State Natural Area (BMSNA) in Alexander
45 County, Caldwell County, and Wilkes County and to add BMSNA to the State Parks System, as
46 provided in G.S. 143B-135.54(b). The State may receive donations of appropriate land and may
47 purchase other needed lands for BMSNA with existing funds in the NC Land and Water Fund,
48 the Parks and Recreation Trust Fund, the federal Land and Water Conservation Fund, and other
49 available sources of funding.
50 SECTION 14.8.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law.
