14 GENERAL ASSEMBLY CONFIRMATION OF ADJUTANT GENERAL
15 SECTION 19.7.(a) G.S. 127A-19 reads as rewritten:
16 "§ 127A-19. Adjutant General.
17 (a) The military head of the militia shall be the Adjutant General who shall hold the rank
18 of major general with federal recognition at time of appointment or attain the rank of major
19 general pursuant to this section. The Adjutant General shall be appointed by the Governor in the
20 Governor's capacity as commander in chief of the militia, in consultation with the Secretary of
21 Public Safety, and shall be subject to confirmation by the General Assembly by joint resolution.
22 The Governor shall submit the name of the person to be appointed, for confirmation by the
23 General Assembly, to the General Assembly by May 1 of the year in which the Adjutant General
24 is to be appointed. If the Governor does not submit the name by that date, the President Pro
25 Tempore of the Senate and the Speaker of the House of Representatives shall submit a name to
26 the General Assembly on or before May 15 of the same year. The appointment shall then be made
27 by enactment of a bill. The bill shall state the name of the person being appointed, the office to
28 which the appointment is being made, the residence of the appointee, and that the appointment
29 is made upon the joint recommendation of the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the
30 President Pro Tempore of the Senate. If there is no vacancy in the office of the Adjutant General
31 and a bill that would confirm the appointment of the person as Adjutant General fails a reading
32 in either chamber of the General Assembly, then the Governor shall submit a new name within
33 30 days.
34 Following appointment pursuant to this section, the Adjutant General shall serve at the
35 pleasure of the Governor. The Adjutant General, while holding this office, shall be a member of
36 the active North Carolina National Guard. If an appointed Adjutant General does not attain the
37 rank of major general with federal recognition within a reasonable period of time from the date
38 of appointment, the Governor shall replace the Adjutant General with an appointee who meets
39 the criteria in in, and is appointed in accordance with, this section. A "reasonable period of time"
40 shall take into account time in grade requirements for promotion or promotions and
41 administrative periods necessary to complete the promotion process.
42 (a1) In case of a vacancy in the office of the Adjutant General, the name of the Adjutant
43 General's successor shall be submitted by the Governor to the General Assembly not later than
44 60 days after the vacancy arises. If a vacancy arises in the office when the General Assembly is
45 not in session, an acting Adjutant General shall be appointed by the Governor to serve pending
46 confirmation by the General Assembly. However, in no event shall an acting Adjutant General
47 serve (i) for more than 12 months without General Assembly confirmation or (ii) after a bill that
48 would confirm the appointment of the person as Adjutant General fails a reading in either
49 chamber of the General Assembly.
50 …."
51 SECTION 19.7.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law.
