37 such examinations and investigations as may be deemed by it necessary to satisfy it that the
38 applicants for admission to the Bar possess the qualifications of character and general fitness
39 requisite for an attorney and counselor-at-law and to this end the Board of Law Examiners shall
40 have the power of subpoena and to summons and examine witnesses under oath and to compel
