37
38 "NOTICE
39
40 CHILD CARE PROVIDER MANDATORY CRIMINAL HISTORY CHECK
41
42 NORTH CAROLINA LAW REQUIRES THAT A CRIMINAL HISTORY RECORD
43 CHECK BE CONDUCTED ON ALL PERSONS WHO PROVIDE CHILD CARE IN A
44 LICENSED CHILD CARE FACILITY, AND ALL PERSONS PROVIDING CHILD CARE IN
45 NONLICENSED CHILD CARE HOMES THAT RECEIVE STATE OR FEDERAL FUNDS.
46 "Criminal history" means a county, state, or federal criminal history of conviction,
47 pending indictment of a crime, or criminal charge, whether a misdemeanor or a felony, that bears
48 on an individual's fitness to have responsibility for the safety and well-being of children. Such
49 crimes include, but are not limited to, the following North Carolina crimes contained in any of
50 the following Articles of Chapter 14 of the General Statutes: Article 6, Homicide; Article 7B,
51 Rape and Other Sex Offenses; Article 8, Assaults; Article 10, Kidnapping and Abduction; Article
