34 SECTION 20.3.(q) G.S. 143B-1208.15, as recodified under subsection (p) of this
35 section, reads as rewritten:
36 "§ 143B-1208.15. Reporting system and database on certain domestic-violence-related
37 homicides; reports by law enforcement agencies required; annual report to the
38 General Assembly.
39 The Department of Public Safety, State Bureau of Investigation (Bureau), in consultation
40 with the North Carolina Council for Women/Domestic Violence Commission, the North Carolina
41 Sheriffs' Association, and the North Carolina Association of Chiefs of Police, shall develop a
42 reporting system and database that reflects the number of homicides in the State where the
43 offender and the victim had a personal relationship, as defined by G.S. 50B-1(b). The information
44 in the database shall also include the type of personal relationship that existed between the
45 offender and the victim, whether the victim had obtained an order pursuant to G.S. 50B-3, and
46 whether there was a pending charge for which the offender was on pretrial release pursuant to
47 G.S. 15A-534.1. All State and local law enforcement agencies shall report information to the
48 Department of Public Safety Bureau upon making a determination that a homicide meets the
49 reporting system's criteria. The report shall be made in the format adopted by the Department of
50 Public Safety. Bureau. The Department of Public Safety Bureau shall report to the chairs of the
