38 SECTION 20.7.(a) Section 7.36(f) of S.L. 2023-134, as amended by Section 3J.17
39 of S.L. 2024-57, reads as rewritten:
40 "SECTION 7.36.(f) Grants for Training to Increase School Safety. – Of the funds
41 appropriated by this act for the grants provided in this section, the Executive Director of the
42 Center for Safer Schools, in consultation with the Department of Health and Human Services,
43 shall award grants to public school units to contract with community partners to address school
44 safety by providing training to help students develop healthy responses to trauma and stress. The
45 training shall be targeted and evidence-based and shall include any of the following services:
46 (1) Counseling on Access to Lethal Means (CALM) training for school health
47 support personnel, local first responders, and teachers on the topics of suicide
48 prevention and reducing access by students to lethal means.
49 (2) Training for school health support personnel on comprehensive and
50 evidence-based clinical treatments for students and their parents or guardians,
51 including any of the following:
