20 SECTION 21.1.(a) Creation of Receipt-Supported Positions Authorized. – The State
21 Capitol Police may contract with State agencies for the creation of receipt-supported positions to
22 provide security services to the buildings occupied by those agencies.
23 SECTION 21.1.(b) Annual Report Required. – No later than September 1 of each
24 fiscal year, the State Capitol Police shall report to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on
25 Justice and Public Safety the following information for the fiscal year in which the report is due:
26 (1) A list of all positions in the State Capitol Police. For each position listed, the
27 report shall include at least the following information:
28 a. The position type.
29 b. The agency to which the position is assigned.
30 c. The source of funding for the position.
31 (2) For each receipt-supported position listed, the contract and any other terms of
32 the contract.
33 SECTION 21.1.(c) Additional Reporting Required Upon Creation of
34 Receipt-Supported Positions. – In addition to the report required by subsection (b) of this section,
35 the State Capitol Police shall report the creation of any position pursuant to subsection (a) of this
36 section to the chairs of the House of Representatives Appropriations Committee on Justice and
37 Public Safety and the Senate Appropriations Committee on Justice and Public Safety and to the
38 Fiscal Research Division within 30 days of the position's creation. A report submitted pursuant
39 to this section shall include at least all of the following information:
40 (1) The position type.
41 (2) The agency to which the position is being assigned.
42 (3) The position salary.
43 (4) The total amount of the contract.
