24 shall provide that transaction fees for electronic payments may be imposed as provided in
25 G.S. 66-58.12, unless otherwise provided for by law. These policies shall be established with the
26 concurrence of the State Treasurer. In addition, any policies that apply to debts payable to or
27 through the office of a clerk of superior court or a magistrate shall be established with the
28 concurrence of the Administrative Officer of the Courts. The Administrative Officer of the Courts
29 may also establish policies otherwise authorized by law that apply to these debts as long as those
30 policies are not inconsistent with the Controller's policies. State agencies shall use the vendor or
31 vendors under the statewide term contract for electronic payments allowed under the policies
32 established under this subsection, unless explicitly exempted by the State Controller, in
33 concurrence with the State Treasurer or the Administrative Officer of the Courts, as applicable.
34 A condition of payment by electronic payment is receipt by the appropriate State agency of
35 the full amount of the account receivable owed to the State agency. A debtor who pays by
36 electronic payment may be required to pay any fee or charge associated with the use of electronic
37 payment.
