20 MODERNIZE AND SIMPLIFY THE STATE HUMAN RESOURCES ACT
21 SECTION 31A.4. By March 15, 2026, the Office of State Human Resources
22 (OSHR) shall submit a report to the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, the Speaker of the
23 House of Representatives, and the Fiscal Research Division with recommended changes to
24 Chapter 126 of the General Statutes to modernize the North Carolina Human Resources Act,
25 simplify its provisions, and align it with contemporary human resources best practices. At a
26 minimum, the report shall address legislative changes needed to:
27 (1) Streamline hiring processes.
28 (2) Enhance recruitment strategies and increase the attractiveness of State
29 government employment.
30 (3) Develop and maintain a high-quality, well-trained State workforce.
31 (4) Improve State employee retention rates.
32 The OSHR shall collaborate with State agencies, local governments, and other
33 relevant stakeholders to develop these legislative proposals.
34
