18 "§ 58-31B-2. Public Property Insurance Enterprise Fund.
19 (a) Creation. – The Public Property Insurance Enterprise Fund is created as a
20 nonreverting enterprise fund, as defined in G.S. 143C-1-3, in the Department of Insurance and
21 to which funds, receipts, transfers, appropriations, contributions, investment earnings, and other
22 income, except for amounts necessary to pay any allowable administration costs or costs
23 associated with payable claims under this Article or Part 1 of Article 31A of this Chapter
24 belonging to the Self-insurance Fund and the Insurance Fund shall be deposited.
25 (b) Investments. – The assets of the Enterprise Fund shall be invested in accordance with
26 the provisions of G.S. 147-69.2 and G.S. 147-69.3.
27 (c) Purpose of Enterprise Fund. – All funds held in the Enterprise Fund are for the
28 purpose of paying claims for damage or loss as a result of any perils for which the Insurance
29 Fund or the Self-insurance Fund is liable. No funds in the Enterprise Fund shall be utilized to
30 purchase any commercial insurance or reinsurance product.
31 (d) Assets. – The assets of the Enterprise Fund shall be used only for the exclusive benefit
32 of the Insurance Fund, the Self-insurance Fund, and entities that have property that is protected
33 against damage or loss by the Insurance Fund or the Self-insurance Fund.
34 "§ 58-31B-5. Actuarial analysis of funds.
35 (a) Annually, the Office of State Fire Marshal shall conduct an actuarial analysis of the
36 Enterprise Fund, the Insurance Fund, and the Self-insurance Fund for the purposes of setting
37 contribution amounts under G.S. 58-31B-30 and premium rates under G.S. 58-31A-40. The State
38 Fire Marshal may contract with a third party or enter into an agreement with another State
39 department, agency, or institution to conduct the actuarial analysis.
40 (b) No later than March 1, a copy of the actuarial analysis conducted under this section
41 shall be submitted to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on General Government and the
42 Fiscal Research Division. This analysis shall be provided upon request to any public education
43 board that participates in the Insurance Fund or any State department, agency, or institution that
44 participates in the Self-insurance Fund.
45 "§ 58-31B-10. Transfers from the Enterprise Fund.
46 Funds shall be transferred from the Public Property Insurance Enterprise Fund to either the
47 Insurance Fund or the Self-insurance Fund, as applicable, upon the processing of a claim in
48 accordance with this Article or Part 1 of Article 31A of this Chapter.
49 "Part 2. Requirements for State Property.
50 "§ 58-31B-20. State Property Self-insurance Fund.
