33 SECTION 35.1.(a) Article 8A of Chapter 65 of the General Statutes is amended by
34 adding the following new sections to read:
35 "§ 65-45. North Carolina Veterans Cemetery Trust Fund.
36 There is hereby established the North Carolina Veterans Cemetery Trust Fund (hereinafter
37 "Fund"), a special fund within the Department of Military and Veterans Affairs. The Fund shall
38 be maintained as a special fund and shall be administered by the Department to carry out the
39 operations and maintenance of the State's veterans' cemeteries. Interest accruing from the monies
40 in the Fund shall be credited to the Fund. The Fund shall consist of the following sources of
41 funding:
42 (1) All interest and investment earnings received on monies in the Fund.
43 (2) Any other funds, as directed by the General Assembly.
44 "§ 65-45.1. Veterans' cemeteries; reporting requirements.
45 Not later than September 15 of each year, the Department of Military and Veterans Affairs
46 shall submit a report to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on General Government, the
47 House Appropriations Committee on General Government, the Senate Appropriations
48 Committee on General Government and Information Technology, and the Fiscal Research
49 Division on all of the following:
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 421

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) The overall condition of each of the State's veterans' cemeteries, including any
2 known issues that require maintenance and/or repair in the upcoming State
3 fiscal year.
4 (2) The total funds spent at each of the State's veterans' cemeteries for
5 maintenance and/or repair and any other expenses in the prior State fiscal year
6 and the source of the funds.
7 (3) The number of full- and part-time employees assigned to work at each of the
8 State's veterans' cemeteries in the prior State fiscal year.
9 (4) The number of veterans and the legal spouses and eligible dependents of
10 veterans who were interred at each of the State's veterans' cemeteries in the
11 prior State fiscal year, and the type of interment for each veteran, legal spouse,
12 and eligible dependent."
