22 PAPER FILING FEE
23 SECTION 37.2.(a) Article 2 of Chapter 55D of the General Statutes is amended by
24 adding a new section to read:
25 "§ 55D-19. Paper filing fee.
26 The Office of the Secretary of State may collect a fee of up to ten dollars ($10.00) each time
27 a document is submitted for filing in typewritten or printed form when that same document could
28 be accepted for filing in electronic form. Funds collected under this section shall be deposited in
29 a new budget fund as created by the Office of State Budget and Management within Budget Code
30 23200 and shall only be used for the following purposes: (i) to support activities that will reduce
31 the processing or response time for services provided by the Office, (ii) to improve or streamline
32 the online filing system maintained by the Office, or (iii) to cover costs directly associated with
33 the handling of mail by the Office."
