46 "§ 147-72.1. Chief Investment Officer.
47 (a) Principal Executive Officer. – The Chief Investment Officer is the Investment
48 Authority's principal executive officer and is responsible to the Board of Directors.
49 (b) Appointment and Term. – The CIO shall be appointed by a majority vote of the Board
50 of Directors, and any vacancy may be so filled by the Board of Directors. An individual appointed
51 as the CIO shall have expert knowledge of investments and a minimum of a 15-year track record
