47 "§ 147-69.2E. Investments in digital assets.
48 (a) The following definitions apply in this section:
49 (1) Designated funds. – Any of the funds described in G.S. 147-69.1(b) and
50 G.S. 147-69.2(a).
Page 450 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (2) Digital asset. – A virtual currency, cryptocurrency, native electronic asset,
2 stablecoin, nonfungible token, or any other asset that is only digital and that
3 confers economic, proprietary, or access rights or powers.
4 (3) Private key. – A unique element of cryptographic data used for signing
5 transactions on a blockchain that is known to the owner of the unique element.
6 (4) Secure custody solution. – A technological product or a blended product and
7 service that employs advanced security measures to safeguard private keys
8 and prevent unauthorized access.
9 (b) The Investment Authority may invest the cash of the designated funds in digital assets
10 only after approval by the Board of Directors. The approval shall be based on an independent
11 assessment by a third-party consultant that all of the following requirements for proposed
12 investments have been met:
13 (1) The digital assets are maintained with a secure custody solution.
14 (2) The potential investment is appropriate for the designated fund's
15 circumstances from a total portfolio perspective.
16 (3) The control environment meets institutional investment industry requirements
17 for independent risk and compliance oversight, operational robustness, and
18 regulatory compliance.
19 (c) An investment in digital assets from any of the designated funds shall not exceed, in
20 the aggregate, five percent (5%) of the balance of the designated fund.
