3 SECTION 41.20.(b) The Director of the Budget is granted flexibility to administer
4 the compensation increases enacted by this act. The State employer contribution rates enacted by
5 this act for retirement and related benefits may be deemed by the Director of the Budget for
6 administrative purposes to become effective after July 1 to provide flexibility in the collection
7 and reconciliation of salary-related contributions as required by law, provided the estimated
8 amount contributed to any affected employee benefit trust equals the amount that would have
9 been contributed to the employee benefit trust if the enacted employer contribution rates had
10 been effective on July 1.
11 SECTION 41.20.(c) This section applies to all employees paid from State funds,
