15 USE OF FUNDS APPROPRIATED FOR LEGISLATIVELY MANDATED INCREASES
16 SECTION 41.21.(a) The Office of State Budget and Management shall ensure that
17 the appropriations made by this act for legislatively mandated salary increases and employee
18 benefits are used only for those purposes.
19 SECTION 41.21.(b) If the Director of the Budget determines that funds appropriated
20 to a State agency for legislatively mandated salary increases and employee benefits exceed the
21 amount required by that agency for those purposes, the Director may reallocate those funds to
22 other State agencies that received insufficient funds for legislatively mandated salary increases
23 and employee benefits.
24 SECTION 41.21.(c) Funds appropriated for legislatively mandated salary and
25 employee benefit increases may not be used to adjust the budgeted salaries of vacant positions,
26 to provide salary increases in excess of those required by the General Assembly, or to increase
27 the budgeted salary of filled positions to the minimum of the position's respective salary range.
28 SECTION 41.21.(d) Any funds appropriated for legislatively mandated salary and
29 employee benefit increases in excess of the amounts required to implement the increases shall be
30 credited to the Pay Plan Reserve.
31 SECTION 41.21.(e) No later than May 1, 2026, the Office of State Budget and
32 Management shall report to the Fiscal Research Division on the expenditure of funds for
33 legislatively mandated salary increases and employee benefits. This report shall include at least
34 the following information for each State agency:
35 (1) The total amount of funds that the agency received for legislatively mandated
36 salary increases and employee benefits.
37 (2) The total amount of funds transferred from the agency to other State agencies
38 pursuant to subsection (b) of this section. This section of the report shall
39 identify the amounts transferred to each recipient State agency.
40 (3) The total amount of funds used by the agency for legislatively mandated salary
41 increases and employee benefits.
42 (4) The amount of funds credited to the Pay Plan Reserve.
