44 MAKE APPLYING FOR STATE JOBS EASIER
45 SECTION 41.21A.(a) Article 5 of Chapter 126 of the General Statutes is amended
46 by adding a new section to read:
47 "§ 126-14.3A. Increasing efficiency of State job application process.
48 (a) The Office of State Human Resources (OSHR) shall streamline the job application
49 process for State positions by enabling applicants to upload resumes or website profiles. An
50 electronic tool shall be utilized to import information from these documents into the State job
51 application format, making the process more efficient while still collecting information necessary
Page 482 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 for merit-based hiring under G.S. 126-14.2 and G.S. 126-14.3. Applicants remain responsible for
2 ensuring all information required for initial screening appears correctly in their completed State
3 job application after importing their resume or profile.
4 (b) For job applications requiring references, supplemental questions, or other
5 information not typically found on resumes and not needed for initial screening, State agencies
6 may collect this information later in the selection process, such as during job interviews.
7 (c) Beginning in 2026 and then annually thereafter, the OSHR shall present the State
8 application form and demonstrate the import process to the State Human Resources Commission
9 to receive the Commission's informal feedback."
10 SECTION 41.21A.(b) The Office of State Human Resources shall modify the State
11 job application process in accordance with this section by no later than November 1, 2025.
12 SECTION 41.21A.(c) This section is effective when it becomes law.
