32 AUTHORIZE STATE AGENCIES TO HIRE ONE OF THE MOST QUALIFIED
33 CANDIDATES FROM A PREVIOUS POSTING
34 SECTION 41.21C.(a) Article 5 of Chapter 126 of the General Statutes is amended
35 by adding a new section to read:
36 "§ 126-14.2A. Hiring candidate from most qualified pool in previous posting.
37 (a) In addition to the authority granted by G.S. 126-3.1, the Council of State, the
38 executive branch agencies, the Community Colleges System Office, and The University of North
39 Carolina are authorized to hire, without posting, into a vacant position if all of the following
40 conditions are met:
41 (1) The employer previously posted for recruitment, in accordance with
42 G.S. 126-7.1 and G.S. 126-14.3, a position that has the same or comparable
43 classification as the position that is currently vacant.
44 (2) The person who is being hired applied for the previous vacant position.
45 (3) The employer selected the person to be in the pool of the most qualified
46 persons for the previous vacant position, in accordance with G.S. 126-14.2,
47 but did not hire that person.
48 (4) For the current vacant position, the person being hired meets the minimum
49 education and experience requirements for the classification and has a salary
50 set within the vacant position's classification range.
