39 GRANT EMPLOYING AGENCY FLEXIBILITY/HIRING/PAY/CLASSIFICATION
40 SECTION 41.21E.(a) Article 1 of Chapter 126 of the General Statutes is amended
41 by adding a new section to read:
42 "§ 126-3.1. Employing agency flexibility.
43 (a) For the purposes of this section, an "employing agency" means the Council of State,
44 State agencies in the executive branch of government, the Community College System Office,
45 and The University of North Carolina.
46 (b) An employing agency is granted flexibility, notwithstanding other provisions of this
47 Chapter to the contrary, to do all of the following:
48 (1) Offer qualified applicants for employment the option to have their
49 applications considered for future positions at the same agency and at other
50 agencies within the same or comparable classification.
