15 PERMANENT HIRING OF CERTAIN EMPLOYEES/SPECIFIC CONDITIONS
16 SECTION 41.21F.(a) Article 1 of Chapter 126 of the General Statutes is amended
17 by adding a new section to read:
18 "§ 126-6.4. Temp-to-perm hiring.
19 (a) The Council of State, the executive branch agencies, the Community College System
20 Office, and The University of North Carolina may directly hire temporary employees into vacant
21 positions if all of the following conditions are met:
22 (1) The permanent position to be filled must be vacant.
23 (2) The temporary employee must have worked for a minimum of six months in
24 a substantially equivalent role with satisfactory performance. This six-month
25 period excludes any mandatory breaks required under G.S. 126-6.3.
26 (3) The temporary employee must meet the minimum education and experience
27 requirements established for the position classification and their salary must
28 be set within the approved classification range.
29 (4) The temporary employee must have been originally hired through the North
30 Carolina Office of State Human Resources Temporary Solutions Program.
31 The Director of the Office of State Human Resources may waive the requirements specified in
32 subdivision (3) of this subsection, including both the minimum education and experience
33 requirements and the requirement that salary be set within the classification range.
34 (b) Except as otherwise provided, a hiring under this section is exempt from the
35 provisions of this Chapter, including any procedural or substantive requirements such as publicly
36 posting the position, requiring a new application, holding a new interview or conducting new
37 reference checks, and following the priorities for certain types of applicants under State law. This
38 exemption for the hiring process does not affect whether the position is subject to this Chapter
39 once the employee is hired.
40 (c) The hiring process authorized under this section is not exempt from the following
41 provisions of this Chapter:
42 (1) G.S. 126-14.
43 (2) G.S. 126-14.1.
44 (3) G.S. 126-14.5.
45 (4) Article 6.
46 (5) Article 7."
47 SECTION 41.21F.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law.
