23 "§ 120-76.1. Prior consultation with the Commission; reporting requirements.
24 (a) The Governor shall consult the Commission before doing any of the following:
25 (1) Authorizing expenditures in excess of the total requirements of a purpose or
26 program as enacted by the General Assembly and as provided by
27 G.S. 143C-6-4.
28 (2) Proceeding to reduce programs subsequent to a reduction of ten percent (10%)
29 or more in the federal fund level certified to a department and any subsequent
30 changes in distribution formulas.
31 (3) Taking measures under Article III, Section 5(3) of the North Carolina
32 Constitution to effect necessary economies in State expenditures required for
33 balancing the budget due to a revenue shortfall, including, but not limited to,
34 (i) making loans among funds, (ii) personnel freezes or layoffs, (iii) capital
35 project reversions, (iv) program eliminations, and (v) use of reserves.
36 However, if the Commission fails to meet within 10 calendar days of a request
37 from the Governor for its consultation, the Governor may proceed to take the
38 actions the Governor deems appropriate and necessary and shall then report
39 those actions at the next meeting of the Commission.
40 (4) Approving a new capital improvement project funded from gifts, grants,
41 receipts, special funds, self-liquidating indebtedness, and other funds or any
42 combination of funds for the project not specifically authorized by the General
43 Assembly. The budget for each capital project must include projected
44 revenues in an amount not less than projected expenditures.
45 …."
