50 DISASTER REIMBURSEMENT REPORTS
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 511

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 SECTION 43.4. Article 2A of Chapter 136 of the General Statutes is amended by
2 adding a new section to read:
3 "§ 136-44.2F. Disaster reimbursement reports.
4 (a) Disaster Detailed Report. – No later than the end of each month, the Department of
5 Transportation shall submit a report to the Joint Legislative Transportation Oversight Committee
6 and the Fiscal Research Division on disaster expenditures that qualify for federal reimbursement.
7 The report shall be categorized by disaster and include the following information:
8 (1) Project number.
9 (2) Project description.
10 (3) Highway division.
11 (4) County.
12 (5) Total project expenditures to date.
13 (6) Federal disaster program eligibility.
14 (7) Estimated expenditures eligible for reimbursement.
15 (8) Date of initial reimbursement submission.
16 (9) Date of last reimbursement submission.
17 (10) Eligible expenditures submitted for reimbursement.
18 (11) Anticipated reimbursement.
19 (12) An explanation if the anticipated amount of reimbursement is less than the
20 estimate of expenditures eligible for reimbursement.
21 (13) Reimbursements received to date.
22 (b) Disaster Summary Report. – No later than the end of each quarter, the Department
23 shall submit a summary report to the Joint Legislative Transportation Oversight Committee and
24 the Fiscal Research Division for all disaster expenditures resulting from a disaster that occurred
25 on or after January 1, 2016, and that qualify for federal reimbursement. The report shall be by
26 disaster and contain the source of federal reimbursement and the total eligible expenditures as of
27 the date of the report.
28 (c) Failure to Submit Report. – If the Department fails to submit a report under this
29 section within 60 days of the required submission date, the Secretary of the Department shall
30 provide to the Joint Legislative Commission on Governmental Operations and the Fiscal
31 Research Division an explanation for not submitting the required report."
