8 DMV LICENSE RENEWAL PRIVATIZATION PILOT PROGRAM
9 SECTION 43.17.(a) Intent. – It is the intent of the General Assembly to evaluate the
10 feasibility, efficiency, customer service impact, and cost-effectiveness of allowing private
11 entities to perform certain functions traditionally administered by the Division of Motor Vehicles
12 of the Department of Transportation (DMV) by implementing pilot programs in Guilford and
13 Harnett Counties authorizing certain third-party vendors to provide drivers license renewal
14 services.
15 SECTION 43.17.(b) RFP Issuance. – No later than January 1, 2026, the DMV shall
16 issue a Request for Proposals (RFP) to solicit bids from third-party vendors to provide renewal
17 services for Class C regular drivers licenses in Guilford and Harnett Counties. The RFP shall
18 require that proposals include, at minimum, the following information:
19 (1) A description of the systems the third-party vendor will implement to comply
20 with:
21 a. All federal requirements and the requirements of Chapter 20 of the
22 General Statutes.
23 b. The DMV's data security protocols.
24 (2) The minimum requirements the third-party vendor will impose for personnel
25 and facilities.
26 (3) Plans for maintaining financial sustainability while providing drivers license
27 renewal services at a cost that does not exceed any fee established by Chapter
28 20 of the General Statutes.
29 (4) A description of performance benchmarks, including, but not limited to,
30 provisions for customer service evaluation and customer complaint resolution,
31 and a plan for submitting quarterly written reports to the DMV evaluating
32 compliance with those benchmarks.
33 (5) A plan for transitioning back to DMV's provision of drivers license renewal
34 services if the pilot program is not continued.
35 SECTION 43.17.(c) Contract Awards and Duration. – No later than July 1, 2026,
36 the DMV shall award one or more contracts to third-party vendors in Guilford and Harnett
37 Counties. The duration of a contract may not extend beyond January 1, 2029.
38 SECTION 43.17.(d) Pilot Program Implementation Date and Requirements. – The
39 pilot program shall begin January 1, 2027, and, notwithstanding any other provision of law, the
40 selected third-party vendors are authorized to issue renewed Class C regular drivers licenses on
41 or after that date. No third-party vendor shall issue a renewed license unless the license meets all
42 of the requirements for renewal pursuant to federal law and Chapter 20 of the General Statutes.
43 A third-party vendor shall not charge any fee for renewal in excess of the fee established by
44 statute.
45 SECTION 43.17.(e) Third-Party Vendor Reporting Requirements. – Each
46 third-party vendor contracting with the DMV pursuant to this section shall quarterly submit a
47 written report to the DMV evaluating compliance with the performance benchmarks established
48 in the RFP.
49 SECTION 43.17.(f) DMV Oversight. – The DMV shall provide oversight of the
50 pilot program, including periodic audits, and may terminate or suspend the participation of any
51 third-party vendor for noncompliance with the General Statutes or any other program
Page 518 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 requirements, including, but not limited to, unsatisfactory customer service or customer
2 complaint resolution.
3 SECTION 43.17.(g) DMV Reporting Requirements. – The DMV shall submit a first
4 report no later than December 31, 2027, and a second report no later than December 31, 2028, to
5 the Joint Legislative Transportation Oversight Committee and the Fiscal Research Division. The
6 reports shall evaluate the pilot program, and, at minimum, include:
7 (1) The number of renewals processed by third-party vendors.
8 (2) An evaluation of each third-party vendor's performance benchmarks.
9 (3) A cost-benefit and efficiency analysis.
10 (4) A description of all audit results.
11 (5) Recommendations regarding the continuation, expansion, or termination of
12 privatized renewal services, including a plan for transitioning back to DMV
13 provision of drivers license renewal services if the pilot program is not
14 continued.
15 SECTION 43.17.(h) State-Offered Services During Pilot Program. – Nothing in this
16 section limits the authority of State-operated DMV offices to provide drivers license renewal
17 services in Guilford and Harnett Counties.
18 SECTION 43.17.(i) Sunset. – This section expires January 1, 2029.
