20 DMV IN-HOME LICENSE RENEWAL PILOT PROGRAM
21 SECTION 43.18.(a) Intent. – It is the intent of the General Assembly to improve the
22 accessibility of and customer service provided by the Division of Motor Vehicles of the
23 Department of Transportation (DMV) by implementing a pilot program in Forsyth County
24 authorizing either the DMV or certain third-party vendors to provide in-home drivers license
25 renewal services. For purposes of this section, the term "in-home drivers license renewal service"
26 means a process by which personnel, employed either by the DMV or a third-party vendor
27 authorized by the DMV, travel to a license holder's residence to conduct the necessary procedures
28 for drivers license renewal.
29 SECTION 43.18.(b) RFP Issuance. – No later than January 1, 2026, the DMV shall
30 issue a Request for Proposals (RFP) to solicit bids from third-party vendors to provide in-home
31 drivers license renewal services for Class C regular drivers licenses in Forsyth County. The RFP
32 shall require that proposals include, at minimum, the following information:
33 (1) A description of the systems the third-party vendor will implement to comply
34 with:
35 a. All federal requirements and the requirements of Chapter 20 of the
36 General Statutes.
37 b. The DMV's data security protocols.
38 (2) The minimum requirements the third-party vendor will impose for personnel
39 and facilities.
40 (3) Plans for acquiring access to the software and equipment necessary to provide
41 in-home drivers license services.
42 (4) Plans for maintaining financial sustainability.
43 (5) A description of performance benchmarks, including, but not limited to,
44 provisions for customer service evaluation and customer complaint resolution,
45 and a plan for submitting quarterly written reports to the DMV evaluating
46 compliance with those benchmarks.
47 SECTION 43.18.(c) Contract Awards and Duration. – No later than July 1, 2026,
48 the DMV shall award one or more contracts to third-party vendors in Forsyth County. The
49 duration of a contract may not extend beyond January 1, 2029.
50 SECTION 43.18.(d) Pilot Program Implementation Date and Requirements. – The
51 pilot program shall begin January 1, 2027, and, notwithstanding any other provision of law, the
