36 SYNCHRONIZED STREETS STUDY
37 SECTION 43.25.(a) The Department of Transportation shall study the effectiveness
38 and implementation of synchronized streets. For the purposes of this section, "synchronized
39 streets" means a street where traffic signals are coordinated to allow vehicles to move through
40 multiple intersections with minimal stops. The study shall:
41 (1) Consider the effectiveness of synchronized streets in areas where they have
42 already been implemented, including the effects implementation has had on
43 (i) motor vehicle safety, ii) motorist travel time, and iii) economic and
44 environmental indicators.
45 (2) Develop criteria for the implementation of synchronized streets, that
46 considers, at minimum:
47 a. Areas where the implementation of synchronized streets in lieu of
48 alternative signaling and improved traffic flow measures would be
49 appropriate.
Page 524 Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 b. The compatibility of synchronized streets with (i) major roads or
2 transportation routes used for commercial or industrial purposes and
3 (ii) vehicles requiring commercial drivers’ licenses.
4 SECTION 43.25.(b) No later than July 1, 2026, the Department shall report the
5 findings of the study required by this section to the Joint Legislative Transportation Oversight
6 Committee and the Fiscal Research Division.
