15 "§ 105-164.13C. Sales and use tax holiday.
16 (a) The taxes imposed by this Article do not apply to any of the following items of
17 tangible personal property if sold between 12:01 A.M. on the first Friday of August and 11:59
18 P.M. the following Sunday:
19 (1) Clothing with a sales price of one hundred dollars ($100.00) or less per item.
20 (2) School supplies with a sales price of one hundred dollars ($100.00) or less per
21 item.
22 (2a) School instructional materials with a sales price of three hundred dollars
23 ($300.00) or less per item.
24 (3) Computers with a sales price of three thousand five hundred dollars ($3,500)
25 or less per item.
26 (3a) Computer School computer supplies with a sales price of two hundred fifty
27 dollars ($250.00) or less per item.
28 (4) Sport or recreational equipment with a sales price of fifty dollars ($50.00) or
29 less per item.
30 (b) The exemption allowed by this section does not apply to any of the following:
31 (1) Sales of clothing accessories or equipment.
32 (2) Sales of protective equipment.
33 (3) Sales of furniture.
34 (4) Repealed by Session Laws 2003-284, s. 45.7, effective October 1, 2003.
35 (5) Sales of an item for use in a trade or business.
36 (6) Rentals.
37 (c) Repealed by Session Laws 2003-284, s. 45.7, effective October 1, 2003."
