23 PART XLV. MISCELLANEOUS
24
25 STATE BUDGET ACT APPLIES
26 SECTION 45.1. The provisions of the State Budget Act, Chapter 143C of the
27 General Statutes, are reenacted and shall remain in full force and effect and are incorporated in
28 this act by reference.
29
30 COMMITTEE REPORT
31 SECTION 45.2.(a) The North Carolina House of Representatives Appropriations
32 Committee Report on the Current Operations Appropriations Act of 2025, Senate Bill 257
33 Proposed Committee Substitute, as amended, which was distributed in the House and used to
34 explain this act, shall indicate action by the General Assembly on this act and shall, therefore, be
35 used to construe this act, as provided in the State Budget Act, Chapter 143C of the General
36 Statutes, as appropriate, and for these purposes shall be considered a part of this act and, as such,
37 shall be printed as a part of the Session Laws.
38 SECTION 45.2.(b) The budget enacted by the General Assembly is for the
39 maintenance of the various departments, institutions, and other spending agencies of the State
40 for the 2025-2027 biennial budget as provided in G.S. 143C-3-5. This budget includes the
41 appropriations of State funds as defined in G.S. 143C-1-1(d)(25).
42 The Director of the Budget submitted a recommended base budget to the General
43 Assembly in the Governor's Recommended Budget for the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium, dated
44 March 2025, and in the Budget Support Document for the various departments, institutions, and
45 other spending agencies of the State. The adjustments to the recommended base budget made by
46 the General Assembly are set out in the Committee Report.
47 SECTION 45.2.(c) The budget enacted by the General Assembly shall also be
48 interpreted in accordance with G.S. 143C-5-5, the special provisions in this act, and other
49 appropriate legislation. In the event that there is a conflict between the line-item budget certified
50 by the Director of the Budget and the budget enacted by the General Assembly, the budget
51 enacted by the General Assembly shall prevail.
Senate Bill 257-Sixth Edition Page 531

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 SECTION 45.2.(d) Notwithstanding subsection (a) of this section, the following
2 portions of the Committee Report are for reference, and do not expand, limit, or define the text
3 of the Committee Report:
4 (1) Summary pages setting forth the enacted budget, the legislative changes, the
5 revised budget, and the related FTE information for a particular budget code
6 and containing no other substantive information.
7 (2) Summary pages setting forth the enacted budget, the legislative changes, the
8 revised budget, and the related FTE information for multiple fund codes
9 within a single budget code and containing no other substantive information.
10
11 REPORT BY FISCAL RESEARCH DIVISION
12 SECTION 45.3. The Fiscal Research Division shall issue a report on budget actions
13 taken by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly. The report shall be in the form of a
14 revision of the Committee Report described in Section 45.2 of this act pursuant to G.S. 143C-5-5.
15 The Director of the Fiscal Research Division shall send a copy of the report issued pursuant to
16 this section to the Director of the Budget. The report shall be published on the General
17 Assembly's internet website for public access.
18
19 MOST TEXT APPLIES ONLY TO THE 2025-2027 FISCAL BIENNIUM
20 SECTION 45.4. Except for statutory changes or other provisions that clearly indicate
21 an intention to have effects beyond the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium, the textual provisions of this
22 act apply only to funds appropriated for, and activities occurring during, the 2025-2027 fiscal
23 biennium.
24
25 APPROPRIATIONS LIMITATIONS AND DIRECTIONS APPLY
26 SECTION 45.5. Except where expressly repealed or amended by this act, the
27 provisions of any legislation enacted during the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly
28 affecting the State budget shall remain in effect.
29
30 EFFECT OF HEADINGS
31 SECTION 45.6. The headings to the Parts, subparts, and sections of this act are a
32 convenience to the reader and are for reference only. The headings do not expand, limit, or define
33 the text of this act, except for effective dates referring to a Part or subpart.
34
35 SEVERABILITY CLAUSE
36 SECTION 45.7. If any section or provision of this act is declared unconstitutional
37 or invalid by the courts, it does not affect the validity of this act as a whole or any part other than
38 the part so declared to be unconstitutional or invalid.
39
40 EFFECTIVE DATE
41 SECTION 45.8. Except as otherwise provided, this act becomes effective July 1,
42 2025.
